Curse of the Crimson Altar is a 1968 British horror film directed by Vernon Sewell and starring Christopher Lee , Boris Karloff , Barbara Steele and Mark Eden .
A Killing Spring is a Canadian TV thriller screened in 2002 , directed by Stephen Williams and starring Wendy Crewson , Kim Schraner .
I 'm Dangerous Tonight is a 1990 American horror television film , directed by Tobe Hooper and starring Mädchen Amick .
The Amazing Mr. Bickford is a video released by Frank Zappa in 1987 , containing orchestral pieces by Zappa set to the clay animation of Bruce Bickford .
Preah Vesandor is a 1993 musical movie starring Tep Rundaro , Pisith Pilika , Oum Sovanny , Ampor Tevi and other stars of the time .

In Greek mythology , Laomedon ( /leɪˈɒmɨdɒn/ ; Ancient Greek : Λαομέδων ) was a Trojan king , son of Ilus , nephew of Ganymede and Assaracus , and father of Priam , Astyoche , Lampus , Hicetaon , Clytius , Cilla , Proclia , Aethilla , Medesicaste , Clytodora , and Hesione .

His elder son was the Rev. Frederic Festus Kelly , vicar of Camberwell , Surrey ( 1838 - -1918 ) , whose children ( his grandchildren ) included the painter Sir Gerald Festus Kelly and Rose Edith Kelly , who married Aleister Crowley .

Joseph Andrew Jackson Lightburn ( September 21 , 1824 -- May 17 , 1901 ) was a farmer , soldier and Baptist Minister , most famous for his service as a Union general during the American Civil War .
Alexander Crawford ( 1842 -- March 17 , 1886 ) was a sailor in the United States Navy who served in the American Civil War .
The Winans Steam Gun was a steam - powered centrifugal gun used during the American Civil War , which used centrifugal forces ( rather than gunpowder ) to propel projectiles .
Karl Buckel ( 12 June 1920 -- 2 September 1997 ) was a highly decorated Hauptmann of the Reserves in the Wehrmacht during World War II and a recipient of the Knight 's Cross of the Iron Cross .
Lieutenant - General John Plumptre Carr Glyn KCB ( 11 January 1837 -- 28 March 1912 ) was a British general who saw active service in the Crimean War and the Anglo - Ashanti War .

Charles Cawetzka ( March 1 , 1877 Detroit , Michigan -- October 23 , 1951 ) was a United States Army soldier received the Medal of Honor for actions on August 23 , 1900 during the Philippine-- American War .
Gerhard Krems ( born 4 May 1920 ) was a highly decorated Oberleutnant in the Luftwaffe during World War II , and a recipient of the Knight 's Cross of the Iron Cross .
Daniel Phineas Woodbury ( 1812 -- August 15 , 1864 ) was an American soldier and an engineer during the American Civil War .
Eduard Skrzipek ( 26 June 1917 -- 25 February 1945 ) was a highly decorated Hauptmann in the Luftwaffe during World War II , and one of only 882 recipients of the Knight 's Cross of the Iron Cross with Oak Leaves .
Gerhard Brenner ( 29 August 1918 -- 29 June 1942 ) was a German World War II Luftwaffe bomber pilot and recipient of the Knight 's Cross of the Iron Cross ( German : Ritterkreuz des Eisernen Kreuzes ) .
Arthur Thomas Thrupp ( 8 June 1828 -- 4 May 1889 ) was an officer of the British Royal Navy during the Crimean War and the Second Opium War , who held several sea commands , including Megaera , which he deliberately beached at the isolated Île Saint - Paul when she became unseaworthy .
Charles Saligny de San - Germano , also called Charles , Baron Saligny , was a French military leader in the French Revolutionary Wars and the Napoleonic Wars .
Sergeant Richard G. Desautels was a United States Army corporal who was captured on December 1 , 1950 at Sonchu by communist forces and not returned by North Korea at the end of the fighting of the Korean War .
Henry F. W. Little ( June 27 , 1842 -- February 7 , 1907 ) was a Sergeant in the 7th New Hampshire Infantry , Union Army , and a Medal of Honor recipient for his actions in the American Civil War .
He was known as Prince Maurice of Battenberg throughout his life , since he died before the British Royal Family relinquished their German titles during World War I and the Battenbergs changed their name to Mountbatten .
Edward Trenchard ( 1785 - -1824 ) was a captain of the United States Navy , who saw service in the Quasi - War with France , the First Barbary War , the War of 1812 , and the Second Barbary War .
Derek Knee ( 22 October 1922 -- 18 March 2014 ) was a British Army intelligence officer during World War II who was the interpreter and translator for Field Marshal Montgomery at the German surrender at Lüneburg Heath in Germany on 3 May 1945 .
In 1250 , only ten years before the battle of Ain Jalut , the same Bahariyya Mamluks ( Qutuz , Baibars and Qalawun ) led Egypt against the Seventh Crusade of King Louis IX of France .
Julius von Verdy du Vernois ( 19 July 1832 -- 30 September 1910 ) , often given the short name of Verdy , was a German general and staff officer , chiefly noted both for his military writings and his service on Graf Moltke 's staff during the Franco - Prussian War .
Rudolf Bacherer ( 19 June 1895 -- 6 July 1964 ) was a highly decorated Oberst of the Reserves in the Wehrmacht during World War II who held several regimental commands .
Private Daniel Farren ( born 1848 -- unknown ) was an Irish - born soldier in the U.S. Army who served with the 8th U.S. Cavalry during the Apache Wars .
Johannes Soodla ( 14 January 1897 in Kudina Parish , ( now in Palamuse Parish ) -- 16 May 1965 ) was an Estonian military officer during World War I , Estonian War of Independence and World War II , serving in Kuperjanov 's Partisan Battalion and the 20th Waffen Grenadier Division of the SS ( 1st Estonian ) .
The Mauser HSc is a 7.65 mm pistol made in Nazi Germany during World War II and post - war .
Pierre Pouyade ( 25 June 1911- 5 September 1979 ) was a French Air Force general , World War II flying ace , and one of the commanders of the Normandie - Niemen squadron .
Adjutant - Chef Antoine Laplasse was a World War I balloon buster and flying ace credited with eight aerial victories , six of which were against observation balloons .
Oberleutnant Walter Ewers ( 11 May 1892 -- 15 May 1918 ) was a World War I flying ace credited with eight aerial victories .
Mato Dukovac ( 23 October 1918 -- September 1990 ) was the leading Croatian fighter ace of World War II , credited with between 40 and 44 confirmed kills .
Between 1912 and 1913 , together with Garegin Nzhdeh , Andranik led a few hundred Armenian volunteers within the Bulgarian army against the Ottomans during the First Balkan War .
Archie Clement ( January 1 , 1846 -- December 13 , 1866 ) , a.k.a . `` Little Arch '' , was a pro - Confederate guerrilla leader in the American Civil War , known for his brutality towards Union soldiers and pro - Union civilians in Missouri .
Christodoulos Hatzipetros ( Greek : Χριστόδουλος Χατζηπέτρος , 1799 - -1869 ) was a Greek military leader during the Greek War of Independence , who became a general and adjutant to King Otto of Greece after Independence .
Georg Hartog Gerson ( 25 August 1788 -- 3 December 1844 ) was a medical doctor and surgeon in the King 's German Legion during the Napoleonic Wars .
General Jacobus Herculaas de la Rey ( 22 October 1847 -- 15 September 1914 ) , known as Koos de la Rey , was a Boer general during the Second Boer War and is widely regarded as being one of the strongest military leaders during that conflict .
Brigadier Duncan Sayre MacInnes CMG DSO ( 21 February 1860 -- 23 May 1918 ) was a Canadian soldier and engineer who served in South Africa before , during and after the Second Boer War .
Johann - Alfred Klaus ( born 4 September 1918 ) was an Oberleutnant in the Luftwaffe during World War II and a recipient of the Knight 's Cross of the Iron Cross .
Kappa Velorum ( κ Vel , κ Velorum ) is a binary star system in the southern constellation of Vela .
NGC 4654 is an intermediate spiral galaxy in the constellation of Virgo at a distance of 55 million light years ( 16.8 megaparsecs ) from the Milky Way that can be spotted with amateur telescopes .
WISEPA J031325.96 + 780744.2 ( designation abbreviated to WISE 0313 + 7807 , or WISE J0313 + 7807 ) is a brown dwarf of spectral class T8.5 , located in constellation Cepheus at approximately 21 light - years from Earth .
50 Cancri ( 50 Cnc , A2 Cancri , A2 Cnc ) is a star in the constellation Cancer .
Zeta Centauri ( ζ Centauri , ζ Cen ) is a binary star system in the southern constellation of Centaurus .
3C 295 is a narrow - line radio galaxy located in the constellation of Boötes .
DDO 169 is an irregular galaxy located in the constellation Canes Venatici .
HIP 70849 is a 10th magnitude K - type main sequence star located approximately 78 light years away in the constellation Lupus .
Iota Gruis ( ι Gru ) is a star in the constellation Grus .
NGC 1156 is a dwarf irregular galaxy in the Aries constellation of the type ibm .
3C 66B is an elliptical Fanaroff and Riley class 1 radio galaxy located in the constellation Andromeda .
2M1207 , 2M1207A or 2MASS J12073346 - 3932539 is a brown dwarf located in the constellation Centaurus ; a companion object , 2M1207b , may be the first extrasolar planetary - mass companion to be directly imaged , and is the first discovered orbiting a brown dwarf .
HD 92589 is a double or multiple star in the constellation Antlia .
HD 14412 ( 22 G. Fornacis ) is the Henry Draper catalogue designation for an ordinary star in the southern constellation Fornax .
Markarian 421 ( Mrk 421 , Mkn 421 ) is a blazar located in the constellation Ursa Major .
51 Eridani is a star in the constellation Eridanus located at RA 04 h 37 m 36.11 s and declination −02 ° 28′ 24.2 `` with an apparent magnitude of 5.22 , meaning it is just visible to the unaided eye in suburban and rural skies .
HD 225218 is a quadruple star system in the northern constellation of Andromeda .
10 Arietis ( abbreviated 10 Ari ) is a binary star in the northern constellation of Aries .
Kelu-1 is a system of two brown dwarfs of spectral types L2 and L4 located in constellation Hydra at approximately 61 light - years from Earth .
Kappa Ursae Majoris ( Kappa UMa , κ Ursae Majoris , κ UMa ) is a binary star in the constellation Ursa Major .
Nu Cancri ( ν Cnc , ν Cancri ) is a star in the constellation Cancer .
40 Arietis ( abbreviated 40 Ari ) is a binary star system in the northern constellation of Aries .
HD 80606 and HD 80607 are two stars comprising a binary star system approximately 190 light - years away in the constellation of Ursa Major .
Gliese 445 ( Gl 445 ) is an M - type main sequence star in the constellation of Camelopardalis , close to Polaris .
Theta Capricorni ( θ Cap , θ Capricorni ) is a star in the constellation Capricornus .

CU Virginis ( CU Vir ) is a star in the constellation Virgo .
HD 83443 b is an extrasolar planet approximately 134 light - years away in the constellation of Vela .
NGC 7814 ( also known as UGC 8 or Caldwell 43 ) is a spiral galaxy about 40 million light - years away in the constellation Pegasus .
47 Boötis or k Boötis is a binary star in the constellation Boötes .
NGC 71 is an Elliptical galaxy ( or possibly a Lenticular galaxy ) in the constellation Andromeda .
IC 2944 , also known as the Running Chicken Nebula or the Lambda Centauri Nebula , is an open cluster with an associated emission nebula found in the constellation Centaurus , near the star Lambda Centauri .
HD 196050 is a star located in the constellation Pavo at a distance of 153 light years or 47 parsecs or 1.45 exameters away from the Solar System .
81 Ceti ( abbreviated 81 Cet ) is the Flamsteed designation of a G - type giant star approximately 300 light years away in the constellation of Cetus .

HD 81101 , also known as k Carinae ( k Car ) , is a star in the constellation Carina .
KELT-2A ( HD 42176A ) is a yellow white dwarf star located about 419 light - years away in the constellation Auriga .
Zeta Caeli ( ζ Cae , ζ Caeli ) is a star in the constellation Caelum .

OGLE - TR-111 is a yellow dwarf star approximately 5,000 light - years away in the constellation of Carina ( the Keel ) .
The Red Spider Nebula ( also catalogued as NGC 6537 ) is a planetary nebula located near the heart of the Milky Way , in the northwest of the constellation Sagittarius .
HD 135438 is a K - type giant star in the northern constellation of Boötes .
Theta Cephei ( θ Cep , θ Cephei ) is a Class A7 , fourth - magnitude star in the constellation Cepheus .
The Jaynes Islands are a cluster of small islands located 37 kilometres ( 20 nmi ) west of the southwest end of Canisteo Peninsula , in the Amundsen Sea off Antarctica .
Lientur Rocks is a group of prominent adjacent rocks lying off the north coast of Robert Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica and extending 660 m ( 722 yd ) in east - west direction and 320 m ( 350 yd ) in north - south direction .
Footscrew Nunatak ( 77 ° 55′S 160 ° 57′E ) is a nunatak 1,865 metres ( 6,120 ft ) high to the southwest of Windy Gully , standing 1.4 nautical miles ( 2.6 km ) southeast of Altar Mountain in the Quartermain Mountains of Victoria Land , Antarctica .
Edwards Point is a rocky point in the south extremity of Kermen Peninsula and Robert Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica .
Goldstream Peak ( 86 ° 41′S 148 ° 30′W ) is a peak rising to about 2,800 metres ( 9,200 ft ) at the junction of ridges from Mount Gjertsen , Mount Grier , and Johansen Peak , in the La Gorce Mountains of Antarctica .
Millington Glacier is a narrow tributary glacier , 10 nautical miles ( 19 km ) long , flowing from the eastern slopes of the Hughes Range , Antarctica , into Ramsey Glacier , northward of Mount Valinski .
Jetsam Moraine ( 76 ° 50′S 161 ° 36′E ) is a thin , sinuous medial moraine that arcs smoothly for 6 nautical miles ( 11 km ) from a point near Mount Razorback to beyond the far ( northeastern ) side of Black Pudding Peak , in the Prince Albert Mountains of Victoria Land , Antarctica .
Mountainview Ridge ( 78 ° 55′S 83 ° 42′W ) is a gentle ice - covered ridge which forms the southeast extremity of Petvar Heights and the Sentinel Range in the Ellsworth Mountains , Antarctica .
Avitohol Point ( Nos Avitohol \'nos a - vi - to-'hol\ ) is a point on the north coast of Livingston Island , Antarctica projecting 1.15 km into Hero Bay to form the west side of the entrance to Skravena Cove and the southeast side of the entrance to Prisoe Cove .
New Swabia ( Norwegian and German : Neuschwabenland ) is a cartographic name sometimes given to an area of Antarctica between 20 ° E and 10 ° W in Queen Maud Land , which is administered as a Norwegian dependent territory under the Antarctic Treaty System .
Mount Hancox ( 72 ° 38′S 166 ° 59′E ) is a prominent mountain , 3,245 metres ( 10,650 ft ) high , about 6 nautical miles ( 11 km ) southeast of Mount Burton , rising above the north margin of Malta Plateau in the Victory Mountains of Victoria Land , Antarctica .
Cape Poinsett ( 65 ° 46′S 113 ° 13′E ) is an ice - covered cape in Antarctica , the northern extremity of Budd Coast , from which the coast recedes abruptly to the southeast and southwest .
Rozier Glacier ( 64 ° 45′S 62 ° 13′W ) is a glacier flowing between Pishtachev Peak and Balis Ridge into Wilhelmina Bay north of Sophie Cliff , on the west coast of Graham Land , Antarctica .
Fry Peak ( 71 ° 3′S 63 ° 40′W ) is a sharp - pointed peak which is the southernmost peak in the Welch Mountains , in Palmer Land , Antarctica .
Paril Saddle ( Parilska Sedlovina \pa-'ril - ska se - dlo - vi-'na\ ) is a saddle of elevation 1390 m in Friesland Ridge in Tangra Mountains on Livingston Island , Antarctica .
Clarsach Glacier ( 69 ° 57′S 70 ° 17′W ) is a glacier flowing south between Prague Spur and the Finlandia Foothills in northern Alexander Island , Antarctica .
Mount Marwick ( 71 ° 2′S 162 ° 48′E ) is a high peak in the Explorers Range of the Bowers Mountains , Antarctica .
Garwood Glacier ( 78 ° 1′S 163 ° 57′E ) is a glacier occupying the northwest part of Garwood Valley , in Victoria Land , Antarctica .
Mount Betty is a small ridge overlooking the Ross Ice Shelf , on the north side of Bigend Saddle , at the north - eastern extremity of the Herbert Range in the Queen Maud Mountains of Antarctica .
The Herschel Heights ( 71 ° 53′S 69 ° 38′W ) are a complex of nunataks of which Mimas Peak on the east is the highest , located southwest of the Enceladus Nunataks and near the head of Saturn Glacier in southeastern Alexander Island , Antarctica .
Cape Howard ( 71 ° 25′S 61 ° 8′W ) is a high , flat - topped , snow - covered cape at the extremity of the peninsula separating Lamplugh Inlet and Odom Inlet , on the east coast of Palmer Land , Antarctica .
Troll Airfield is an airstrip located 6.8 kilometres ( 4.2 mi ) from the research station Troll in Princess Martha Coast in Queen Maud Land , Antarctica .
Eliza Rocks is a chain of rocks lying between Desolation Island and Zed Islands off the north coast of Livingston Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica and extending 1 km in west - northwest direction .
Haas Glacier ( 85 ° 45′S 164 ° 55′W ) is a steep tributary glacier draining northward from Rawson Plateau to enter the south side of Bowman Glacier , in the Queen Maud Mountains of Antarctica .
Isingufsa Bluff ( 72 ° 21′S 1 ° 13′E ) is a rock bluff forming the northeast corner of Isingen Mountain in the Sverdrup Mountains of Queen Maud Land , Antarctica .
Klevekampen Mountain ( 71 ° 58′S 7 ° 41′E ) is a large , mainly ice - free mountain 3 nautical miles ( 6 km ) east of Kubus Mountain in the Filchner Mountains of Queen Maud Land , Antarctica .
The Japanese Antarctic Research Expedition ( JARE ) was an ecological expedition studying the ecosystems near Showa Station in Antarctica .
Moutonnée Lake is a sub - glacial lake that lies within Moutonnee Valley , marginal to the George VI Ice Shelf , 7 km ( 4.3 mi ) south of Ablation Point indenting the east coast of Alexander Island , facing the west coast of Palmer Land , Antarctica .
Mount Osborne ( 78 ° 37′S 84 ° 47′W ) is a mountain ( 2,600 m ) standing 5 nautical miles ( 9 km ) east of Mount Craddock , at the end of a side ridge running from the latter and featuring Sanchez Peak and Stolnik Peak , in the Sentinel Range , Ellsworth Mountains , Antarctica .
Heidemann Glacier is a glacier , 5 nautical miles ( 9 km ) long , originating close northwest of Mount Damm in the Queen Elizabeth Range of Antarctica and flowing east into Lowery Glacier .
Mount Crean is one of the westernmost peaks in the dry valley region of South Victoria Land in Antarctica .
Hyde Glacier ( 79 ° 48′S 83 ° 42′W ) is a short glacier flowing east through the Edson Hills to join Union Glacier , in the Heritage Range , Antarctica .
Taylor Rookery is an emperor penguin breeding colony on the Mawson Coast of Mac . Robertson Land in East Antarctica .
Keltie Head ( 63 ° 47′S 57 ° 41′W ) is a rounded headland with vertical cliffs which rise to a small ice dome 395 metres ( 1,300 ft ) high , forming the northwestern end of Vega Island , south of Trinity Peninsula , Antarctica .
Gregory Point is a rocky point on the northwest coast of Smith Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica projecting 700 m into Drake Passage .
Lepitsa Peak ( Bulgarian : връх Лепица , `` Vrah Lepitsa '' \'vr&h le-'pi - tsa\ ) is the ice - covered peak rising to 1110 m in the northeast foothills of Detroit Plateau on Trinity Peninsula in Graham Land , Antarctica .
Croatia ( i / kroʊˈeɪʃə/ kroh - AY - shə ; Croatian : Hrvatska ( xř̩ʋaːtskaː ) ) , officially the Republic of Croatia ( Croatian : Republika Hrvatska , listen ) , is a sovereign state at the crossroads of Central Europe , Southeast Europe , and the Mediterranean .
Mills Peak ( 74 ° 14′S 163 ° 54′E ) is a sharp peak in the Deep Freeze Range of Victoria Land , Antarctica .
The Pearl Rocks are a group of rocks covering an area 6 km ( 3.7 mi ) by 4 km ( 2.5 mi ) close off the west coast of Tower Island in the Palmer Archipelago of Antarctica .
The Teniente R. Marsh Airport is the northernmost airport in the continent of Antarctica .
Half Century Nunatak ( 85 ° 22′S 178 ° 50′W ) is a prominent nunatak , displaying a high east - facing rock escarpment , located 4 nautical miles ( 7 km ) north of Dismal Buttress at the west side of upper Shackleton Glacier , Antarctica .
Nuñez Point ( 65 ° 33′S 64 ° 15′W ) is a point forming the west extremity of Takaki Promontory on Barison Peninsula on Graham Coast , Graham Land , in Antarctica .
Kip Peak ( 84 ° 31′S 164 ° 28′E ) is a summit rising to over 3,000 metres ( 10,000 ft ) , located 3 kilometres ( 2 mi ) northeast of Tempest Peak on a northeast trending ridge , in the Queen Alexandra Range of Antarctica .
Maigo Peak ( 68 ° 8′S 42 ° 42′E ) is a rocky hill situated 1.5 nautical miles ( 3 km ) east - southeast of Cape Hinode and just west of the Bōhyō Heights on the coast of Queen Maud Land , Antarctica .
Mount McCoy ( 75 ° 52′S 141 ° 10′W ) is a high table - topped massif with dark , snow - free , vertical walls , at the east side of Land Glacier in Marie Byrd Land , Antarctica .
Sierra Island ( 62 ° 24′S 59 ° 48′W ) is a narrow island which is marked by a series of small elevations throughout its length , lying 0.5 miles ( 0.8 km ) northwest of Dee Island and north of Greenwich Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica .
Mackin Table is an ice - topped , wedge - shaped plateau , about 20 nautical miles ( 37 km ) long , standing just north of Patuxent Ice Stream in the Patuxent Range of the Pensacola Mountains , Antarctica .
Rojas Peak ( 64 ° 49′S 62 ° 55′W ) is a peak in Antarctica rising to about 675 m in the center of Lemaire Island , Danco Coast , Graham Land .
Hatch Plain ( 80 ° 44′S 25 ° 36′W ) is a small debris - covered area at about 1,350 metres ( 4,430 ft ) , on the eastern margin of the Du Toit Nunataks , in the Read Mountains of the Shackleton Range , Antarctica .
Mount Hulshagen ( 72 ° 31′S 31 ° 16′E ) is a mountain , 2,100 metres ( 6,900 ft ) high , standing 1 nautical mile ( 2 km ) northwest of Mount Bastin on the north side of the Belgica Mountains , Antarctica .
Currituck Island ( 66 ° 5′S 100 ° 40′E ) is an island in Antarctica 7 nautical miles ( 13 km ) long marked by numerous small coves , lying on the northwest side of Edisto Channel in the Highjump Archipelago .
Greene Point is an ice - covered point 7 nautical miles ( 13 km ; 8.1 mi ) northeast of Andrus Point in Lady Newnes Bay , Victoria Land , Antarctica .
Bonnier Point ( 64 ° 28′S 63 ° 57′W ) is a headland forming the west extremity of Obitel Peninsula and marking the north side of the entrance to Hamburg Bay , on the northwest coast of Anvers Island in the Palmer Archipelago , Antarctica .
Knobhead ( 77 ° 55′S 161 ° 34′E ) is a massive ice - free mountain , 2,400 metres ( 7,900 ft ) high , standing south of the western end of the Kukri Hills and overlooking Ferrar Glacier and Taylor Glacier at their point of apposition , in Victoria Land , Antarctica .
Wulfila Glacier ( Lednik Wulfila \'led - nik vul-'fi - la\ ) is located on the southern slopes of Breznik Heights , Greenwich Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica , south - southwest of Solis Glacier and west of Zheravna Glacier .
Kubusdalen ( 71 ° 58′S 7 ° 14′E ) is an ice - filled valley between Trollslottet Mountain and Kubus Mountain in the Filchner Mountains of Queen Maud Land , Antarctica .
Marr Bluff ( 69 ° 47′S 69 ° 20′W ) is an exposed , rocky bluff , 1,065 metres ( 3,500 ft ) high , immediately north of Wager Glacier on the east coast of Alexander Island , Antarctica .
Willan Saddle ( Sedlovina Willan \se - dlo - vi-'na ' wi - l&n\ ) is a flat , crescent - shaped and ice - covered saddle extending 1 km in the northeast - southwest direction between Burdick South Peak and Willan Nunatak in eastern Livingston Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica .
The Robertson Islands or Robertsons Islands are a group of islands extending 6 km southward of the south - eastern extremity of Coronation Island in the South Orkney Islands of Antarctica .
Livingston Island ( historical Russian name Smolensk , 62 ° 36′S 60 ° 30′W ) is an Antarctic island in the South Shetland Islands , Western Antarctica lying between Greenwich Island and Snow Islands .
Mathieu Rock ( 66 ° 20′S 136 ° 49′E ) is an ice - free rock , midway between Cape Bickerton and Rock X , at the east side of the entrance to Victor Bay , Antarctica .
The Balaena Islands are a small group of rocky islands lying close to the coast of Antarctica , 10 nautical miles ( 19 km ) northeast of Cape Folger .
Cape Morse ( 66 ° 15′S 130 ° 10′E ) is a low , ice - covered cape which marks the east side of the entrance to Porpoise Bay and forms the division between Banzare Coast and Clarie Coast in Wilkes Land , Antarctica .
Elsner Ridge ( 71 ° 47′S 167 ° 21′E ) is a narrow , southwest - trending ridge , or spur , 6 nautical miles ( 11 km ) long , located 4 nautical miles ( 7 km ) northeast of the south end of the Homerun Range in the Admiralty Mountains of Victoria Land , Antarctica .
Reuning Glacier ( 71 ° 26′S 72 ° 41′W ) is a glacier situated on the north side of Beethoven Peninsula , lying within the southwest portion of Alexander Island , Antarctica .
Mount Rosenwald ( 85 ° 4′S 179 ° 6′W ) is a mountain ( 3,450 m ) which forms a distinctive landmark between the heads of Gallup and Baldwin Glaciers in the Queen Maud Mountains of Antarctica .
Johns Knoll ( 71 ° 59′S 7 ° 59′E ) is a crevassed ice knoll ( apparently the ice surface reflection of the underlying rock ) in the lower part of Vinje Glacier in Queen Maud Land , Antarctica .
Glopeflya Plain ( 72 ° 7′S 10 ° 25′E ) is a narrow , ice - covered plain between the eastern part of the Orvin Mountains and the interior ice plateau which rises close southward , in Queen Maud Land , Antarctica .
Nødtvedt Nunataks ( 86 ° 32′S 162 ° 18′W ) is an isolated nunataks standing in mid - stream of the Amundsen Glacier , rising 7 nautical miles ( 13 km ) east - northeast of Mount Bjaaland , Antarctica .

Meena Shorey ( 1921 - -1989 ) was an Indian cinema and later Pakistani cinema actress , who worked in Hindi / Urdu and Punjabi films .
Oswaldo Payá Sardiñas ( 29 February 1952 -- 22 July 2012 ) was a Cuban political activist .
David Wolffsohn ( Yiddish : דוד וואלפסאן‎ ; Hebrew : דוד וולפסון‎ ; 9 October 1856 , Darbėnai ( Polish : Dorbiany ) , Kovno Governorate - 15 September 1914 ) was a Lithuanian - Jewish businessman , prominent early Zionist and second president of the Zionist Organization ( ZO ) .
Zbigniew Karkowski ( born 14 March 1958 -- 12 December 2013 ) was a Polish experimental musician and composer .
Jeff Crouch ( 7 August 1934 -- 5 August 1994 ) was a leading Australian rules football field umpire in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) in the 1960s , and 1970s .
Lobby Loyde ( born John Baslington Lyde , 18 May 1941 -- 21 April 2007 ) , also known as John Barrie Lyde or Barry Lyde , was an Australian rock music guitarist , songwriter and producer .
George Buchanan ( Scottish Gaelic : Seòras Bochanan ; February 1506 -- 28 September 1582 ) was a Scottish historian and humanist scholar .
Jacob Floris van Langren ( c. 1525 - 27 July 1610 ) was a Dutch cartographer and globe - maker who established a family dynasty of three generations in those professions .
Lovisa von Burghausen ( 1698 -- 20 January 1733 ) was a Swedish memoirist who became famous for her story about her time in captivity as a slave in Russia after being taken prisoner by the Russians during the Great Northern War .
David Cox ( 9 July 1809 -- 6 December 1885 ) , known as David Cox the Younger , David Cox II or David Cox Jr. to distinguish him from his better - known father David Cox , was an English painter in watercolour , mostly of landscapes .
Lemvo Jean Abou Bakar Depara , known as Depara ( 1928 - -1997 ) , was an Angolan - born photographer who worked in the Democratic Republic of Congo .
Mrinalini Sarabhai ( 11 May 1918 -- 21 January 2016 ) was an Indian classical dancer , choreographer and instructor .
Rosemond Mountain or Rosemond Wilkinson ( died 3 July 1841 ) was a British actress .
Gil Jae or Kil Jae ( 1353 - -1419 ) was a Neo - Confucian scholar , politician , and writer of Korea 's Goryeo Dynasty and early Joseon Dynasty .
José Carlos Rodrigues ( 1844 - -1922 ) was a Brazilian journalist , financial expert , and philanthropist , with connections to both the United States and Great Britain .
Jukka Tapanimäki ( 11 August 1961 -- 1 May 2000 ) was a Finnish game programmer .
Raoul Paoli ( 24 November 1887 -- 23 March 1960 ) was a French athlete , boxer , rower and actor .
Newton Smith Fielding ( 1799 - -1856 ) , was an English painter and lithographer .
John Harris Browne ( 22 April 1817 -- 12 January 1904 ) , generally referred to as J. Harris Browne , was an explorer in Australia and a pioneer pastoralist .
Margareta Sofia Lagerqvist ( 1771 -- 6 June 1800 , in Norrköping ) was a noted Swedish opera singer and stage actress .
Sheikh Emad Effat ( c. 1959 -- 2011 ) was a senior Egyptian Sunni Islamic cleric at al - Azhar Mosque who was shot and killed during protest demonstrations 15 December 2011 .
Alice Jamieson ( 1860 - 1949 ) was an American Calgary , Alberta feminist and magistrate .
Cellach mac Máele Coba ( died 658 ) was an Irish king and is said to have been High King of Ireland .
Paul Waymond Caine ( 1891 -- 1931 ) was a founder of Kappa Alpha Psi Fraternity , Incorporated .
Alice Thomas Ellis ( born Anna Margaret Lindholm , 9 September 1932 -- 8 March 2005 ) was a British writer and essayist .
Pacificus Baker , O.F.M. ( 1695 - -1774 ) , was an English Minorite friar and noted Catholic spiritual writer of the 18th century .
Hagbarth Schjøtt , Jr. ( 25 February 1920 -- 2001 ) was a Norwegian resistance member during World War II and later businessperson .
Blessed Jordan of Pisa ( or Giordano da Pisa ) ( c. 1255 -- 19 August 1311 ) was a Dominican theologian and preacher , the first whose vernacular Italian sermons are preserved .
Zha Fuxi ( Chinese : 查阜西 ; 1895 - -1976 ) , also known as Zha Yiping ( 查夷平 ) was a leading player and scholar of the guqin .
John Darcy , 1st Baron Darcy de Knayth ( c. 1290 -- 30 May 1347 ) was an English peer .
Lawrence Stenhouse ( 29 March 1926 - 1982 ) was a British educational thinker who sought to promote an active role for teachers in educational research and curriculum development .
Mieczysław Dziemieszkiewicz , ps . Rój ( 25 January 1925 -- 14 April 1951 ) --
Henry Clay Fry ( 1840 -- 1929 ) was an American entrepreneur in the glass industry in the late nineteenth century and early twentieth century .
Jack Deas ( 5 November 1875 -- 23 August 1949 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with South Melbourne , Fitzroy and Essendon in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Andreas Laskaratos ( Greek : Ανδρέας Λασκαράτος ; 1 May 1811 -- 23/24 July 1901 ) was a satirical poet and writer from the Ionian island of Cefalonia ( or Kefallinia ) , representative of the Heptanese School ( literature ) .
Peter Dale Wimbrow , usually known as Dale Wimbrow , ( June 6 , 1895 -- 1954 ) was an American composer , radio artist and writer .
Sir Piers Crosby ( 1590 - 1646 ) was an Irish soldier and politician .
Mary Ann Lawrenson , née Molyneux ( 1850 - 1943 ) was an English activist in the co - operative movement .
William Sotwell ( 1571 - -1639 ) was an English landowner and politician who sat in the House of Commons between 1621 and 1624 .
Matthew Nicholas ( 1594 - -1661 ) was an English Dean of St. Paul 's Cathedral , London .
August Enna ( 13 May 1859 -- 3 August 1939 ) was a Danish composer , known mainly for his operas .
Alexander Leeper ( 3 June 1848 -- 6 August 1934 ) , was an Australian educationist .
Marjorie Fleming ( also spelt Marjory ; 15 January 1803 -- 19 December 1811 ) was a Scottish child writer and poet .
General Joseph Yorke , 1st Baron Dover KB , PC ( 24 June 1724 -- 2 December 1792 ) , styled The Honourable Joseph Yorke until 1761 and The Honourable Sir Joseph Yorke between 1761 and 1788 , was a British soldier , diplomat and Whig politician .
Linus Parker ( 23 April 1829 -- 5 March 1885 ) was a Bishop of the Methodist Episcopal Church , South , elected in 1882 .
Carl Gustaf Ekman ( 6 October 1872 -- 15 June 1945 ) was a Swedish politician , Member of Parliament 1911 - 1932 ( both lower and upper houses ) , leader of the Freeminded People 's Party 1924 - 1932 and Prime Minister from 1926 to 1928 and again from 1930 to 1932 .
Gundemar was a Visigothic King of Hispania , Septimania and Galicia ( 610 - -612 ) .
John William Foster ( 1745 -- January 1809 ) , of Rosy Park , was an Anglo - Irish volunteer and politician .
Kurt Blasberg ( 14 July 1902 -- 15 December 1967 ) was a German naval officer and group leader in the 36 .
Dr. Gad Rausing ( 19 May 1922 -- 28 January 2000 ) was a Swedish industrialist and archaeologist .
George Littlewood ( 1859 - -1912 ) was a professional pedestrian .
Sir Henry Dymoke , 1st Baronet ( 1801 -- 28 April 1865 ) , was a British landowner and the hereditary King 's Champion .
Gistemar , Ghislemar , or Gilmer ( died 684 ) was briefly the mayor of the palace in Neustria and Burgundy after deposing his father Waratton in 682 .
Harriet Slater CBE ( née Evans ; 1903 -- 12 October 1976 ) was a British Labour and Co - operative politician .
General Sir William Erskine Baker KCB ( 29 November 1808 -- 16 December 1881 ) was a senior British Indian Army officer who went on to be Military Secretary to the India Office .
Lars Larsson Eldstierna ( originally Eld ) ( c. 1623 - -1701 ) was a Swedish landshövding ( governor ) and the founder of the noble family of Eldstierna .
Philipp Schall von Bell ( died 1560 ) was the commander - in - chief ( Landmarschall ) of the Livonian Order forces during the first two years of the Livonian War ( 1558 - -1583 ) .
Harry Toole ( 7 September 1897 -- 13 August 1958 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Carlton in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Wayne Crouse ( 16 December 1924 - 19 May 2000 ) was the viola professor emeritus at the University of Oklahoma and principal violist of the Oklahoma City Philharmonic from 1982 until his death from cancer at the age of 75 .
Simon Lowth ( 1636 - -1720 ) was an English nonjuring clergyman , nominated by James II as Dean of Rochester , and later a controversialist on the position of bishops .
Anton Anderson ( 1892 - -1960 ) was chief engineer of the Alaska Railroad and served as Mayor of Anchorage , Alaska from 1956 to 1958 .
Henry Gough - Calthorpe , 1st Baron Calthorpe ( 1 January 1749 -- 16 March 1798 ) , known until 1796 as Sir Henry Gough , 2nd Baronet , was a British politician .
Robert Ransome ( 1753 -- 7 March 1830 ) was an English maker of agricultural implements .
Reccared II ( in Spanish , Galician and Portuguese , Recaredo ) , ( ? -- 16 April 621 ) was Visigothic King of Hispania , Septimania and Galicia briefly in 621 .
Pierre Lalouette de Vernicourt ( 1711 - 1792 ) was a distinguished French anatomist .
Fatma Aliye Topuz ( 9 October 1862 -- 13 July 1936 ) , often known simply as Fatma Aliye or Fatma Aliye Hanım , was a Turkish novelist , columnist , essayist , women 's rights activist and humanitarian .
Weng Wenhao ( simplified Chinese : 翁文灏 ; traditional Chinese : 翁文灝 ; pinyin : Wēng Wénhào ; 1889 -- 27 January 1971 ) was a Chinese geologist , educator , and paramount politician .
Captain Samuel Brady ( 1756 - -1795 ) was a frontier scout , notorious Indian fighter , and the subject of many legends , in the history of western Pennsylvania and northeastern Ohio .
John Hesselius ( 1728 - -1778 ) was a portraitist who worked mostly in Virginia and Maryland .
Colonel Shafaat Jamil ( Bengali : শাফায়াত জামিল ) , Bir Bikram ( 1 March 1940 - 11 August 2012 ) a career Bangladesh Army officer , was Commanding Officer of the 3rd East Bengal Regiment of Z Force Brigade in Sector 11 of Bangladesh Forces during the War of Bangladesh Independence in 1971 .
Michael Rabbet ( or Rabbett ) ( c. 1562 -- 5 February 1630 ) was an English clergyman and translator of the Authorised King James Version of the Bible .
Abraham Stupp ( Hebrew : אברהם סטופ‎ , 1897 -- 26 September 1968 ) was an Israeli politician who served as a member of the Knesset for the General Zionists between 1951 and 1955 .
Enrico Lorenzetti ( 4 January 1911 -- 8 August 1989 ) was an Italian professional Grand Prix motorcycle road racer who competed in the 1940s and 1950s .
Paweł Działyński ( Latin : Paulus Dzialinski ; born 1560 -- died 1609 ) of Ogończyk coat of arms , was a Polish courtier , royal secretary , ambassador and governor of Bobrowniki and Radziejów .
Nathaniel Wheeler ( b. Watertown , Litchfield county . , Connecticut , Sept. 7 , 1820 ; d. Bridgeport , Dec. 31 . 1893 ) was an American manufacturer and legislator .
Professor Frederick William Shotton FRS ( 1906 - -1990 ) was a British geologist .
Tiziano Pagan De Paganis ( Verona , 1858 -- Bologna , 1932 ) was an Italian painter , mainly of landscapes and genre subjects .
Philipp Foltz ( 11 May 1805 -- 5 August 1877 ) was a German historical painter , born at Bingen .
Achille Brocot ( pronounced `` broco '' ) ( 11 July 1817 -- 19 January 1878 ) was a French clockmaker and amateur mathematician .
Henry Joseph Grayson ( 9 May 1856 -- 21 March 1918 ) was a British - born Australian nurseryman and scientist , best known as the designer of a machine for ruling diffraction gratings .
Yisrael Guri ( Hebrew : ישראל גורי‎ , born Yisrael Gurfinkel in 1893 , died 17 September 1965 ) was an Israeli politician who served as a member of the Knesset for Mapai between 1949 and 1965 .
Hippolyte Lippens ( 16 October 1847 -- 31 December 1906 ) was a lawyer , manager of sugar factories and a Belgian liberal politician .
Alonso de Reinoso ( or Reynoso ) ( 1518 - -1567 ) was a Spanish Conquistador in Honduras , Mexico , Peru and Chile .
George Sava ( 1903 - -1996 ) was a British surgeon and prolific writer of Russian origin .
James McLaren Henderson ( 1 May 1907 -- 5 March 2009 ) , better known as Mac Henderson was a Scottish international rugby union player and businessman , founding one of Edinburgh 's most famous restaurants , Henderson 's .
Kreeta Haapasalo , or Kantele - Kreeta ( 13 November 1813 - 29 March 1893 ) , was a Finnish kantele - player , singer and folk musician .
Michael Clemente ( August 29 , 1908 -- December 1987 ) , also known as `` Mike Costello '' and `` Big Mike '' , was a New York mobster with the Genovese crime family who became a major force in controlling the East River waterfront of Manhattan from the 1950s to 1979 .
Bjørn Gunnar Olsen ( 1942 -- 1992 ) was a Norwegian journalist , novelist , playwright and biographer .
Captain Gallagher ( died 1818 ) was an Irish highwayman who , as one of the later Irish Rapparees ( guerrillas ) , led a bandit group in the hills of the Irish countryside , armed with a blunderbuss , of the day , during the late 18th and early 19th century .
Edward Frederick Sanderson ( 1874 - -1955 ) was a Congregational minister who served in Beverly , Massachusetts , Central Congregational Church in Providence , Rhode Island and at Plymouth Church of the Pilgrims in Brooklyn Heights , New York .
Christine Marion Fraser ( 24 March 1938 -- 22 November 2002 ) was a Scottish author of popular fiction .
Joe Avezzano ( 17 November 1943 -- 5 April 2012 ) was an American football player and coach .
Máirtín Ó Cadhain ( ( ˈmɑːrtʲiːnʲ oː ˈkainʲ ) ; 1906 -- 18 October 1970 ) was one of the most prominent Irish language writers of the twentieth century .
Grand Ayatollah Mirza Mohsen Koochebaghi Tabrizi ( 9 January 1924 -- 3 August 2011 ) was an Iranian Twelver Shi'a Marja .
Per Olof Arne Palmqvist , born 28 May 1921 in Brunflo , Jämtland , died 15 January 2003 in Uppsala .
Stanhope Aspinwall ( born 5 July 1713 in Liverpool , England and died on 17 January 1771 ) was a British diplomat .
Ta'isi Olaf Frederick Nelson , ( 24 February 1883 - 28 February 1944 ) , also known as Ta'isi O. F. Nelson , was a successful businessman and one of the founding leaders of the Mau movement for Samoan independence from colonial rule .
Hugh Curwen ( died 1 November 1568 ) was an English ecclesiastic and statesman .
Sir Herbert Ashcombe Walker , KCB ( 15 May 1868 -- 29 September 1949 ) was a British railway manager .
Fred Cairns ( 1857 Scotland -- 1 April 1896 , Johannesburg , South Africa ) was a well - known British comedian and music hall artist of the Victorian age .
Christina Nilsdotter ( died 1399 ) was a Swedish singer and song teacher .
Leandro Gallerano ( fl . 1615 - 1632 ) was an Italian composer .
Neville Waller ( 17 September 1932 -- 10 January 1998 ) was an Australian rules footballer , who played in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Salih Gjuka ( 1876 - 1925 ) was an Albanian teacher and activist of the Albanian National Awakening .
Sadettin Heper ( 1899 - -1980 ) was a composer of Turkish music considered as an important link to the world of Turkish Mevlevi music before the foundation of the Turkish Republic in 1923 .
Charles Rattray Smith M.A. ( Aberdeen ) died at his residence `` Tremenheere '' , 16 McClelland Street , Willoughby on 10 June 1941 aged 81 years .
Licerio Gerónimo ( August 27 , 1855 - -January 16 , 1924 ) was a general of the Philippine Revolutionary Forces under Emilio Aguinaldo .
Juana Galán ( 1787 - -1812 ) , nicknamed La Galana , was a guerrilla fighter of the Peninsular War ( 1808 - -1814 ) who took to the street to fight against the French cavalry that tried to pass through the town of Valdepeñas .
Toros Toramanian ( Armenian : Թորոս Թորամանեան ; 1864 -- March 1 , 1934 ) was a prominent Armenian architect and architectural historian .
Sir John Lloyd , 1st Baronet ( ca . 1617 -- 1 January 1664 ) was a Welsh politician who sat in the House of Commons at various times between 1646 and 1660 .
Georges Chanot III ( 11 January 1831 - -11 March 1895 ) was a French luthier ( or violin - maker ) who ran a successful business in London in the late 19th - century .
John Bryn Roberts ( 8 January 1843 -- 14 April 1931 ) was a Welsh lawyer , later a judge and Liberal politician .
Dominick Dubh Lynch , died 14 August 1508 , second Mayor of Galway .
Francis Dalzell Finlay ( 1793 - -1857 ) , was an Irish journalist .
Colonel Frederick R. De Funiak , formerly superintendent of machinery for the Louisville & Nashville , died at his residence in Louisville , Kentucky , on March 29 , 1905 at age 65 .
Adolph von Morlot ( also : Charles Adolph de Morlot ; see Note 1 ) ( 5 April 1820 - 10 February 1867 ) was a scientist who specialized in geology and later in archaeology .
Marcello Siniscalco ( 31 July 1924 -- 29 November 2013 ) was an Italian scientist at the forefront of the development of the nascent field of genetics .
Sir John Glanville the younger ( 1586 - -2 October 1661 ) , was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons at various times between 1614 and 1644 .
Gareth Hoskins OBE ( 15 April 1967 -- 9 January 2016 ) was a Scottish architect .
Abraham Kenneth Snowman CBE FSA ( 26 July 1919 -- 9 July 2002 ) was a British jeweller , painter and chairman of Wartski .
Greville Phillimore ( 1821 - 1884 ) was a priest of the Church of England and hymnal compiler .
Preben von Ahnen ( 18 September 1606 -- 15 November 1675 ) was a German - born civil servant and landowner in Norway .
Robert Clutterbuck ( 1772 - -1831 ) was an English antiquary and topographer .
Valerio Belli ( c. 1468 -- 1546 ) , also known as Valerio Vicentino , was a celebrated medallist and gem engraver , who with Giovanni Bernardi , who was twenty years younger , was the leading specialist in intaglios engraved in rock crystal , a difficult luxury form which Belli pioneered .
Gentile Virginio Orsini ( c. 1434 -- 8 January 1497 ) was an Italian condottiero and vassal of the papal throne and the Kingdom of Naples , mainly remembered as the powerful head of the Orsini family during its feud with Pope Alexander VI ( Rodrigo Borgia ) .
Surgeon General George Bidie CIE ( 3 April 1830 -- 19 February 1913 ) was a British physician who worked in India in the Madras Medical Service .
Frederik Carl Gram Schrøder ( 19 July 1866 -- 13 August 1936 ) , usually referred to as F.C.G. Schrøder and also known as Fritz Schrøder was a Danish civil servant , Governor of Danmarks Nationalbank from 1925 and until his death .
Pier Francesco Garoli or Caroli ( 1638 - -1716 ) was an Italian painter , active in painting
William Keith Relf ( 22 March 1943 -- 14 May 1976 ) was an English musician , best known as the lead vocalist and harmonica player for The Yardbirds .
Johan Fridolf Hagfors ( 11 March 1857 - -18 August 1931 ) was a Swedish newspaper publisher , music critic and composer , most known for having composed the two songs Modersmålets sång ( The mother tongue 's song ) and Ålänningens sång ( Song of the Ålender ) .
Val Duncan ( 4 May 1884 -- 20 May 1960 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Fitzroy in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Umar Bakkalcha ( 1953 ? - 1980 ) was one of the early Oromo nationalists and martyrs well - remembered in the Chercher highlands of Harerghe especially for the heroic speeches he made at his death spot .
Sir Marmaduke Roydon ( also Rawdon and Rawden , with Royden a contemporary spelling ) ( 1583 -- 1646 ) was an English merchant - adventurer and colonial planter , known also as a Royalist army officer .
Saints Chrysanthus and Daria ( 3rd century -- c. 283 ) are saints of the Early Christian period .
Basil Hansen ( 7 October 1926 -- 2 January 2015 ) was an Australian ice hockey player .
Sir Tej Bahadur Sapru , KCSI , PC ( Kashmiri : तेज बहादुर सप्रू ( Devanagari ) , تیج بہادر سپرو ( Nastaleeq ) ) ( 8 December 1875 -- 20 January 1949 ) was an Indian lawyer and politician .
Grigory Mairanovsky ( 1899 , Batumi -- 1964 ) was a Soviet biochemist and poison developer .
Ryszard Bakst ( 4 April 1926 -- 25 March 1999 ) was a Polish pianist and distinguished piano teacher .
Thomy Lafon ( 1810 - 1893 ) was a Creole businessman , philanthropist and human rights activist in New Orleans , Louisiana , USA .
Rambo Rajkumar , born Rajkumar ( 21 October 1956 -- 26 April 2009 ) , was an Indian fight master / action choreographer .
Ralph Thoresby ( 16 August 1658 -- 16 October 1725 ) was an antiquarian , who was born in Leeds and is widely credited with being the first historian of that city .
Vasant Chavan ( 1942 - 11 July 2006 ) was a member of Rajya Sabha from Maharashtra state during the terms 25 April 2005 to 2 April 2006 as Nationalist Congress Party candidate , in bye - elections unopposed after the resignation of then Shiv Sena Rajya Sabha member Sanjay Nirupam .
Manuel Alcón ( died 1962 ) was an Argentine film actor and musician of the classic era .
Zakhary Chepiha ( Ukrainian : Чепіга Харитон Олексійович ) , also known as Kharyton ( Kharko ) Chepiga ( Russian : Захарий Алексеевич Чепега)(1725 - 14 January 1797 ) was , after Sydir Bily , the second Kosh ataman of the Black Sea Cossack Host .
Alessandro Poglietti ( early 17th century -- July 1683 ) was a Baroque organist and composer of unknown origin .
Stanko Prek ( 1915 , Solkan near Nova Gorica -- 1999 , Ljubljana ) was a classical guitarist and composer from Slovenia .
Jovan Maleševac ( Serbian Cyrillic : Јован Малешевац ; fl . 1524 - -1562 ) was a Serbian Orthodox monk and scribe who collaborated in 1561 with the Slovene Protestant reformer Primož Trubar to print religious books in Cyrillic .
Ernest Sloman was the Dean of St George 's Cathedral , Georgetown , Guyana from 1910 until his death in 1918 .
Daniel Brevint or Brevin ( baptised 11 May 1616 -- 5 May 1695 ) was Dean of Lincoln from 1682 to 1695 .
Shah Mohammad ( 1780 - -1862 ) ( Punjabi : ਸ਼ਾਹ ਮੁਹੰਮਦ/شاہ محمّد ) was a Punjabi poet who lived during the reign of Maharaja Ranjit Singh and is best known for Jangnama which depicts the First Anglo - Sikh War that took place after the death of Maharaja Ranjit Singh .
Jacobus Clemens non Papa ( also Jacques Clément or Jacob Clemens non Papa ) ( c. 1510 to 1515 -- 1555 or 1556 ) was a Netherlandish composer of the Renaissance based for most of his life in Flanders .
Sir Edwin Pears ( 18 March 1835 -- 27 November 1919 ) was a British barrister , author and historian .
Lewis Gordon , 3rd Marquess of Huntly ( c. 1626 - -1653 ) was a Scottish nobleman .
John of Tours or John de Villula ( died 1122 ) was a medieval Bishop of Wells in England who moved the diocese seat to Bath .
Madhava Ashish ( 1920 - -1997 ) was a Scottish born naturalized Indian spiritualist , mystic , writer and agriculturist , known for his services to Indian agriculture .
Allan Segal ( 16 April 1941 -- 8 February 2012 ) was a BAFTA - winning documentary film maker .
Maharaja Shri Immadi Chikka Krishnaraja Wadiyar II ( Kannada : ಇಮ್ಮಡಿ ಕೃಷ್ಣರಾಜ ಒಡೆಯರ್ , -- 25 April 1766 ) , was also known popularly as Immadi Krishnaraja Wadiyar II . He was the titular ruler of the Kingdom of Mysore from 1734 to 1766 .
Jakub Ostroróg ( c. 1516 - 1568 ) was a prominent 16th - century Polish magnate and politician from Poznań .
Iskandar Thani Alauddin Mughayat Syah ( 1610 - 15 February 1641 ) was the thirteenth sultan of Aceh , following the powerful Iskandar Muda .
Alexandr Innokentevich Tolmatchew , also transliterated Tolmachev ( Russian : Александр Иннокентьевич Толмачёв , 21 September 1903 , St. Petersburg 16 November 1979 , Leningrad ) was a twentieth century Russian and Soviet botanist and phytogeographer who was a leading expert in the flora of Russia 's Arctic .
Jan Michał Rozwadowski ( 7 December 1867 -- 13 March 1935 ) was a Polish linguist and a professor at the Jagiellonian University .
Imperial Iranian General Samad Samadianpour ( 1919 - 1982 ) was the Chief of Police of Iran during Mohammad Reza Shah Pahlavi 's reign .
Rick Lomba ( 1950 - -1994 ) was a South African documentary filmmaker , environmentalist and Carte Blanche cameraman .
Ivo Kolin ( 1924 , Zagreb - 2007 , Zagreb ) was a Croatian economist , engineer and inventor .
Hugh Quincy Alexander ( 7 August 1911 -- 17 September 1989 ) was a Democratic U.S. Representative from North Carolina between 1953 and 1963 .
Robert Sidaway ( 14 January 1758 -- 13 October 1809 ) , a convict of the First Fleet , was transported to Australia for stealing in 1788 .
François Sébastien Charles Joseph de Croix , Count of Clerfayt ( 14 October 1733 -- 21 July 1798 ) , a Walloon , joined the army of the Habsburg Monarchy and soon fought in the Seven Years ' War .
Ichadon ( 501 - -527 ) , also known as Geochadon ( 거차돈 ) or by his courtesy name Yeomchok ( 염촉 ) or Yeomdo , was a Buddhist monk and advisor to the Silla king Beopheung .
Nicholas Barnewall , 3rd Viscount Barnewall ( 15 April 1668 -- 14 June 1725 ) was an Irish nobleman .
Sinmu of Silla ( r. 839 , died 839 ) ( born Ujing ) was the 45th monarch of the Korean kingdom of Silla .
Soyen Shaku died peacefully on 29 October 1919 in Kamakura .
Leslie Lloyd Rees ( properly surnamed Lloyd - Rees , but sometimes called Rees ; 14 April 1919 - 4 July 2013 ) was variously Honorary Chaplain to the Queen , Chaplain - General of Prisons and Anglican Bishop of Shrewsbury .
Michel - Joseph Gebauer ( 1763 -- December 1812 ) was a French oboist , violinist , viol player , bandmaster , and composer .
Peter Levathes ( 28 July 1911 - 9 January 2002 ) was an American film and advertising executive , best known for briefly running 20th Century Fox .
Arthur J. Lamb ( 12 August 1870 -- 10 August 1928 ) was a British lyricist best known for the 1897 song `` Asleep in the Deep '' and the 1900 song `` A Bird in a Gilded Cage '' .
Sir Christopher Hatton KG ( 1540 -- 20 November 1591 ) was an English politician , Lord Chancellor of England and a favourite of Elizabeth I of England .
Egide Fologne ( 1830 - 1919 ) was a Belgian entomologist who specialised in microlepidoptera .
John Dallachy ( c. 1808 -- 4 June 1871 ) was a curator of Melbourne Botanic Gardens and a plant collector .
Yosef Sprinzak ( Hebrew : יוסף שפרינצק‎ ; 8 December 1885 -- 28 January 1959 ) was a leading Zionist activist in the first half of the 20th century , an Israeli politician , and the first Speaker of the Knesset , a role he held from 1949 until his death in 1959 .
Victor Engström ( 25 April 1989 -- 1 July 2013 ) was a Swedish bandy player who played for Västerås SK as a midfielder or forward .
Des Raj Goyal ( 1929 - 2013 ) , also known as Desraj Goyal or D. R. Goyal , is an Indian journalist , academic and a well - known author of books on secularism and communalism .
Kenneth Lee Spencer ( 25 April 1913 - 25 February 1964 ) , usually known as Kenneth Spencer , was an African - American opera singer and actor .
W. Maynard Sparks ( 16 December 1906 -- 17 August 1999 ) was an American Bishop of the Evangelical United Brethren Church ( E.U.B. ) and of the United Methodist Church , elected in 1958 .
Arthur Bartlett Maurice ( 1873 - -1946 ) was an American editor , born in Rahway , New Jersey , and educated at Richmond College ( VA ) , and at Princeton .
Wu Fuheng ( Chinese : 吴富恒 ; Pinyin : Wú Fùhéng ; 1911 - -2001 ) was the president of Shandong University from December 1979 to June 1984 .
Alick Grant ( 11 August 1916 -- 2008 ) was an English footballer who played in the Football League for Aldershot , Leicester City , Derby County , Newport County , York City .
Shalini Moghe ( 1914 - 2011 ) was an Indian educationist , social worker and the founder of Kasturba Kanya School for tribal children and Bal Niketan Sangh , the first Montessori school in the state of Madhya Pradesh .
Air Marshal Sir John Frederick Andrews Higgins KCB , KBE , DSO , AFC , RAF ( 1 September 1875 -- 1 June 1948 ) was a senior officer in the Royal Flying Corps , serving as a brigade commander from 1915 to 1918 .
Somerset Lowry - Corry , 2nd Earl Belmore ( 11 July 1774 -- 18 April 1841 ) , styled The Honourable from 1781 to 1797 and then known as Viscount Corry to 1802 , was an Irish nobleman and politician .
Lin Shihong ( 林士弘 ) ( died 622 ) was an agrarian leader who rose against the rule of the Chinese Sui Dynasty near the end of Emperor Yang 's reign .
Thomas Osborne , 1st Duke of Leeds , KG ( 20 February 1632 -- 26 July 1712 ) , English statesman ( commonly known as Lord Danby and ( Marquess of ) Carmarthen when he was a prominent political figure ) , served in a variety of offices under Kings Charles II and William III of England .
Air Chief Marshal Sir Leslie Norman Hollinghurst GBE KCB DFC ( 2 January 1895 -- 8 June 1971 ) , was a British First World War Flying Ace who later became an Air Chief Marshal in the RAF .
Ödön Beniczky de Benice et Micsinye ( 12 February 1878 -- 20 January 1931 ) was a Hungarian legitimist politician , who served as Interior Minister between 1919 and 1920 .
Akinpelu Oludele Adesola ( November 1927-May 2010 ) was a Nigerian professor of Surgery , educational administrator and former Vice chancellor of the University of Lagos .
Leo Mishkin ( January 22 , 1907 - December 27 , 1980 ) was a well - known American film , theater , and television critic of the mid-20th century .
Marcello Viotti ( 29 June 1954 -- 16 February 2005 ) was a Swiss classical music conductor , best known for opera .
Lemma Barkaloo ( 1840 - -1870 , aka Lemma Barkeloo ) was the first woman in America to attend law school .
Guy Innes ( 1879 - -1953 ) was an Australian journalist who was the editor of The Herald newspaper in Melbourne between 1918 and 1921 .
Cor Melchers ( 1954 -- 15 September 2015 ) was a Dutch painter .
Tô Ngọc Vân ( 15 December 1906 or 1908 - -17 June 1954 ) , also known as Tô Tử , was a Vietnamese painter .
Badr al - Din Lu'lu ' ( Arabic : بدر الدين لؤلؤ‎ ) ( died 1259 ) was successor to the Zangid rulers of Mosul , where he governed in variety of capacities for half a century .
Mr. Willem Frederik Ewald Marggraff ( 9 June 1923 , Vught -- 7 December 2003 , Vught ) was a controversial wealthy son of a famous family of Dutch nobility .
Buddhaghosa Mahasthavir ( Devanagari : बुद्धघोष महास्थविर ) ( born Sapta Ratna Vajracharya ) ( 12 October 1921 - 24 September 2011 ) was a Nepalese Buddhist monk who worked to revive Theravada Buddhism in Nepal in the 1940s in the face of suppression by the Rana regime .
William David Davies , often known as W. D. P. Davies , ( 18 January 1897 -- 7 July 1969 ) was a Welsh Presbyterian minister and writer on theological topics .
Robertson Buchanan ( 1770 - -1816 ) was a Scottish civil engineer from Glasgow .
Jaime de la Té y Sagau ( Barcelona , 1684 - Lisbon , 1736 ) was a Spanish composer active at the court of King Joao V in Lisbon .
William Pattenden ( born 31 October 1747 at East Peckham , Kent ; died 1817 at Hadlow and buried 2 April 1817 at East Peckham ) was an English professional cricketer who played for Kent .
Major Alfred Whitmore ( 1876 - -1946 ) was an English pathologist who , together with C.S. Krishnaswami , identified Burkholderia pseudomallei , the causative agent of melioidosis ( also known as `` Whitmore 's disease '' ) in opium addicts in Rangoon in 1911 .
Johann Daniel Mylius ( ca . 1583 -- 1642 ) was a composer for the lute , and writer on alchemy .
Eric Palante ( 21 January 1963 -- c. 9 January 2014 ) was a Belgian motorcycle off - road rally racer .
Augustine Phillips ( died May 1605 ) was an Elizabethan actor who performed in troupes with Edward Alleyn and William Shakespeare .
Nicholas III , Lord of Mecklenburg ( after 1230 -- 8 June 1289 or 1290 ) was from 1264 to 1289 Lord of Mecklenburg .
Sam Gravenall ( 18 July 1885 -- 8 March 1948 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with St Kilda in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Solomon Golub ( Latvia , 27 February 1887 - Bronx , New York , 18 June 1952 ) was a Russian - born , naturalized American , song composer .
The Very Reverend Philip Ruh , O.M.I. ( born Philip Roux ; 6 August 1883 -- 24 October 1962 ) was Catholic priest and church architect .
Walter Lax ( 22 March 1912 -- q2 1967 ) was an English footballer who scored 16 goals from 98 appearances in the Football League playing for Lincoln City , Blackpool and York City .
Colin Ward ( 14 August 1924 -- 11 February 2010 ) was a British anarchist writer .
Orley May ( February 16 , 1897 - January 1968 ) was an American detective in Cleveland , Ohio in the 1930s .
Alexander Bruce , 2nd Earl of Kincardine FRS ( 1629 - -1681 ) was a Scottish inventor , politician , judge and freemason , responsible for developing the pendulum clock , in collaboration with Christiaan Huygens .
Aefgen Listincx , or Aeff Pietersdochter ( died 20 August 1538 ) , was a Dutch anabaptist and prophet .
Eric the Victorious ( Old Norse : Eiríkr inn sigrsæli , Modern Swedish : Erik Segersäll ) ( 945 ? -- c. 995 ) was the first Swedish king ( c. 970 - -995 ) about whom anything definite is known .
Jean O'Hara ( 1913 -- 1973 ) was a famed prostitute in Honolulu 's `` vice district '' during World War II . Born Betty Jean O'Hara in Chicago , Illinois , she was the only child of strict Catholic parents .
John Cooper Wiley ( September 26 , 1893-February 3 , 1967 ) was a United States Foreign Service officer and ambassador .
Ramón Quián ( died May 26 , 2006 ) , better known as Monguito `` El Único '' , was a Cuban vocalist , bandleader , producer and composer .
George Foster Pierce ( 1811 - -1884 ) was an American bishop of the Methodist Episcopal Church , South elected in 1854 .
Syd Dyer ( 25 May 1916 -- 7 April 1976 ) , also referred to as Sid Dyer , was an Australian rules footballer who played for North Melbourne in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Sarah Killgore Wertman , née Sarah Killgore ( 1 March 1843 , Clinton County , Missouri - 21 May 1935 , Seattle ) was an American lawyer .
Bhanubhakta Acharya ( Nepali : भानुभक्त आचार्य ; 1814 -- 1868 ) was a Nepalese poet who translated the great epic Ramayana from Sanskrit to Nepali language .
Che Kam Kong ( died in 1871 ) , also known as Chea Kunkong , was a Chinese Protestant Christian who was killed because of his beliefs in China .
Ada Patterson ( 5 July 1867 -- 26 June 1939 ) was an American print journalist .
Thomas Ulick Burke ( 1826 - 1867 ) was a well - known figure in gold - rush Victoria , Australia , famous as the victim of the `` Break O ' Day '' aka `` Scarsdale '' aka `` Piggoreet '' murder .
Paul Joseph Constantin Gabriël or Paul Gabriël ( 5 July 1828 -- 23 August 1903 ) was a painter , draftsman , watercolorist , and etcher who belonged to the Hague School .
Pekka Erkki Juhani Tammilehto ( 27 October 1952 -- 13 August 2011 ) , better known by his stage name Topi Sorsakoski , was a Finnish singer .
George H. Chirgwin ( 14 December 1854 - - 17 November 1922 ) was a British music hall star billed as `` the White - Eyed Kaffir '' , a black face minstrel act .
John Tayloe I ( 15 February 1688 -- November 1747 ) was one of the richest plantation owners and businessmen in Virginia for his generation .
Henrietta Shore ( January 22 , 1880 -- 1963 ) was a Canadian - born artist who lived a large part of her life in the United States , most notably California .
Joseph Whiteside ( 4 August 1906 -- October 1990 ) was an English competition swimmer who represented Great Britain in the Olympics , and England in the British Empire Games , during the late 1920s and early 1930s .
Zhao Deyin ( 趙德諲 ) ( died 892 ) , formally the Prince of Huai'an ( 淮安王 ) , was a warlord late in the Chinese dynasty Tang Dynasty , who initially served as a general under the pretender emperor Qin Zongquan .
Glenda Reiser , ( 16 June 1955 -- 6 January 2008 ) was a Canadian middle - distance runner .
Richard Courtney died on Saltspring Island , British Columbia on 16 August 1997 .
Eric Edgar Cooke ( 25 February 1931 -- 26 October 1964 ) , nicknamed the `` Night Caller '' , was an Australian serial killer .
Colin Welland ( 4 July 1934 -- 2 November 2015 ) , born Colin Edward Williams , was a British actor and screenwriter .
Gad Frederik Clement , generally known as G. F. Clement ( 1867 - -1933 ) , was a Danish painter .
Arthur Beardmore ( died 1771 ) was an English lawyer and a friend of John Wilkes .
Frans Mostaert ( 1528 - -1560 ) was a Flemish Renaissance painter specializing in landscape paintings .
Madge Tennent ( 22 June 1889 -- 5 February 1972 ) was a naturalized American artist , born in England , raised in South Africa , and trained in both France and Australia .
Archibald Montgomerie , 11th Earl of Eglinton ( 18 May 1726 -- 30 October 1796 ) was a Scottish General , and Member of Parliament ( MP ) in the British Parliament .
Vince Griffiths ( 29 May 1901 -- 7 January 1967 ) was a Welsh rugby union player who represented Wales and the British Lions .
Gedong Bagus Oka ( October 3 , 1921 -- November 14 , 2002 ) was a Hindu reformer and philosopher in Indonesia .
Lieutenant - General John Cutts , 1st Baron Cutts PC ( Ire ) ( 1661 -- 25 January 1707 ) , British soldier and author , came from an Essex family .
Harvey Lowe ( 30 October 1918 -- 11 March 2009 ) was a Canadian radio presenter and world yo - yo champion .
Henry Cecil Leon ( 19 September 1902 -- 23 May 1976 ) , who wrote under the pen - names Henry Cecil and Clifford Maxwell , was a judge and a writer of fiction about the British legal system .
Neville Blyth ( March 1825 -- 15 February 1890 ) was a South Australian colonial politician .
Bradford Torrey ( 9 October 1843 in Weymouth , Massachusetts -- 7 October 1912 ) was a United States ornithologist .
Father Charles Roger Tennant ( Tasmania , 8 April 1919 - 30 June 2003 ) was an Anglican Priest , biographer of Joseph Conrad , and historian of Korea .
Samuel Kaylin ( 18 January 1892 -- 7 July 1983 ) was a film composer who scored Charlie Chan and Mr. Moto movies for 20th Century Fox .
Walter Van Dyke ( 1823 - -1905 ) was a Los Angeles County Superior Court judge and a justice of the California Supreme Court in the late 19th and early 20th centuries .
Gerry Livingston continued as the honorary chairman until his death in 1988 .
Boris Christoff ( Bulgarian : Борис Кирилов Христов , official transliteration Boris Kirilov Hristov pronounced ( ˈbɔris ˈkirilɔf ˈxristɔf ) ; 18 May 1914 -- 28 June 1993 ) was a Bulgarian opera singer , widely considered to have been one of the greatest basses of the 20th century .
Michael Glawogger ( 3 December 1959 -- 23 April 2014 ) was an Austrian film director , screenwriter and cinematographer .
William Goldwyer ( August 1829 - -13 November 1864 ) was a police officer and explorer in colonial Western Australia .
William Ewart Hart ( 20 April 1885 - 29 July 1943 ) was an Australian aviator and dentist .
Merle Oberon ( born Estelle Merle O'Brien Thompson , 19 February 1911 -- 23 November 1979 ) was an Anglo - Indian actress .
Sir Edward Smith , 1st Baronet ( c.1630 - 6 September 1707 ) was an English landowner and politician who sat in the House of Commons in 1653 .
Zha Jizuo ( 1601 - -1676 ) was a Chinese writer and scholar who lived in the late Ming dynasty and early Qing dynasty .
Gerard Piel ( 1 March 1915 in Woodmere , N.Y. -- 5 September 2004 ) was the publisher of the new Scientific American magazine starting in 1948 .
Hulagu Khan , also known as Hülegü or Hulegu ( Mongolian : Хүлэгу хаан ; Chagatai : ہلاکو ; Persian : هولاکو خان‎‎ ; Chinese : 旭烈兀 ; c. 1218 -- 8 February 1265 ) , was a Mongol ruler who conquered much of Western Asia .
Gert Jonke ( 8 February 1946 -- 4 January 2009 ) was an Austrian poet , playwright and novelist .
Sir Wilfrid Lawson , 1st Baronet , of Brayton ( 5 October 1795 -- 12 June 1867 ) , was an English landowner , businessman and investor in the new industrial age .
Elisabeth Helene von Vieregg ( 4 May 1679 -- 27 June 1704 ) , Countess of Antvorskov , was a Danish noble and lady - in - waiting of German origin .
Anders Venger ( 5 January 1872 -- 23 February 1935 ) was Norwegian Minister of Agriculture in 1923 and 1923 - 1924 , as well as head of the Ministry of Education and Church Affairs in 1923 , and Minister of Labour in 1926 .
Gregor Hradetzky ( 31 January 1909 -- 29 December 1984 ) was an Austrian canoer and organ builder who competed in the late 1930s .
Edward Potts Cheyney , A.M. , LL.D. ( 1861 - -1947 ) was an American historical and economic writer , born at Wallingford , Pennsylvania .
Arthur C. Sidman ( August 3 , 1863 -- 16 August 1901 ) was the son of a blacksmith who became a popular American vaudeville performer and playwright .
Hong Dae - yong ( Hangul : 홍대용 ; hanja : 洪大容 ; 12 May 1731 -- 17 November 1783 ) , styled Damheon ( Hangul : 담헌 ; hanja : 湛軒 , `` Relaxed house '' ) was a philosopher , astronomer and mathematician of the late Joseon Kingdom .
Volodymyr Malyk ( Ukrainian : Володимир Малик ; real name Volodymyr Sychenko ; born 21 February 1921 in Kiev Oblast , Ukrainian SSR , died 31 August 1998 ) is a Soviet / Ukrainian writer .
Emmeline Lewis Lloyd ( 18 November 1827 -- 22 September 1913 ) was an early British alpine mountaineer .
Sir Joseph Robert Archibald Glenn , OBE ( 24 May 1911 -- 4 January 2012 ) was an Australian industrialist and founding Chancellor of La Trobe University .
Princess Augusta of Saxe - Gotha - Altenburg ( 30 November 1719 -- 8 February 1772 ) was Princess of Wales between 1736 and 1751 , and Dowager Princess of Wales thereafter .
Heinrich Carl von Schimmelmann died - as the richest man in Denmark - in Copenhagen on 15 February 1782 , at the age of 58 .
Cheng Wenshan ( Chinese : 成文山 ; pinyin : Chéng Wénshān ; 11 October 1929 -- 9 July 2008 ) was a Chinese educator who served as President of Hunan University between 1982 to 1987 .
Alan Gordon Gutteridge ( 4 February 1892 -- February 1942 ) was an Australian civil engineer and a founder of Gutteridge Haskins & Davey ( now known as the GHD Group ) .
Bo Gabriel Montgomery also known as Bo - Gabriel de Montgomery ( born 21 April 1894 in Stockholm , Sweden - died 16 October 1969 in Nyköping , Södermanland , Sweden ) was a political writer , social commentator and genealogist .
Penumarti Viswanatha Sastry ( Telugu : పెనుమర్తి విశ్వనాథశాస్త్రి ) ( 2 May 1929 -- 25 December 1998 ) was a famous Telugu writer and editor .
Thomas Maurice ( 1754 - -1824 ) was a British oriental scholar and historian .
James Thraves ( 1869 -- 1936 ) was an English footballer who played in the Football League for Leicester Fosse and Notts County .
Hugh Primrose Lindsay ( 31 October 1765 -- 23 April 1844 ) was a British naval captain , Chairman of the East India Company and Member of Parliament .
Hugh Galbraith ( 22 December 1868 -- 1930 ) was a Scottish footballer , most notable as a player for Luton Town .
Paul Alexiu ( 1893 - -1963 ) was the Major - General in the Romanian Armed Forces during World War II . He served as Commanding Officer of the 4th Artillery Regiment between 1941 and 1942 , and in 1942 to 1943 he served as the Commanding Officer of the artillery 10th division .
Leonard Raven - Hill ( 10 March 1867 - 31 March 1942 ) was an English artist , illustrator and cartoonist .
Mar Ignatius Michael IV Daher ( or Zahir , 1761 - -1816 ) was the Patriarch of the Syriac Catholic Church from 1801 to 1810 .
Jindřich Zelený ( 13 November 1922 -- 11 September 1997 ) ( translation : Henry Green ) was a Czech philosopher and the author of several books .
António de Mariz Carneiro ( 15 ? ? in Lisbon -- 1642 ) was a Portuguese nobleman who served as the official cosmographer to the Portuguese crown .
Generalmajor Heinz Brandt ( 11 March 1907 -- 21 July 1944 ) was a German Wehrmacht staff officer who served during World War II as an aide to Generalleutnant Adolf Heusinger , who was the head of the operations unit of the General Staff .
Alan Fields ( 29 March 1914 -- 21 February 1998 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Fitzroy in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) during the 1940s .
( David ) Eifion Evans ( 22 January 1911 -- 23 May 1997 ) was Archdeacon of Cardigan from 1967 to 1979 .
Dr. Ding Lik - kiu ( Chinese : 陳立僑 , 1921 in Sarawak , British Malaya -- 24 June 2008 in San Francisco , United States ) was a prominent Hong Kong social activist in the 1970s to 80s .
Ibrahim Saeed , sometimes spelled as Sayeed ( 20 May 1945 -- 27 May 2007 ) , was an Indian writer and publisher .
Major General Janaka Perera , RWP , RSP , VSV , USP , VSP , rcds , psc , CR ( 1 February 1946 -- 6 October 2008 ) was a Sri Lankan General and politician .
Edwin Richard Hallifax ( 1874 - -1950 ) was a senior official in Hong Kong in the early 20th century .
Paskal Sotirovski , PhD ( Macedonian : Паскал Сотировски ; b. 23 November 1927 in Vrben , Gostivar - d. 20 January 2003 in Paris , France ) was a famous Macedonian astrophysicist , specialist in Solar Physics .
Jan Romer ( 1869 in Lwów -- 1934 in Warsaw ) was a Polish general and military commander .
Dr James Augustus Rooth ( 1868 - -1962 ) was a colonel of the Royal Army Medical Corps , a member of the Royal College of Surgeons , and house surgeon at the Radcliffe Infirmary , Oxford .
Maicon Pereira de Oliveira ( 8 May 1988 -- 8 February 2014 ) commonly known as Maicon , was a Brazilian footballer who played in the Ukrainian Premier League for most of his professional career .
Bulo C Rani ( 6 March 1920 -- 24 March 1993 ) was a prominent Indian music director .
Fred Raymond aka Raimund Friedrich Vesely ( 20 April 1900 -- 10 January 1954 ) was an Austrian composer .
Guy Le Borgne ( 6 January 1920 -- 12 December 2007 ) was a French Army general that fought in World War II , First Indochina War and Algerian War .
Sir Lawrence Weaver ( 1876 - -1930 ) was a British architectural writer and civil servant .
Ulick Óge Burke , 8th lord of Clanricarde , died 1519 .
Heiner Fleischmann ( 2 February 1914 -- 25 December 1963 ) was a German motorcycle racer before and after World War II . Fleischmann raced mainly for the NSU company .
José María Luengo Martínez ( 1896 - -1991 ) was a Spanish writer and archaeologist .
Stephen Michael Elonka ( - 1983 ) was the author of numerous technical books , including Standard Plant Operators ' Manual .
Oleksa Dovbush ( Ukrainian : Олекса Довбуш ) ( born 1700 , Pechenizhyn Kolomyia-- died 24 August 1745 ) was a famous Ukrainian outlaw , leader of opryshky , who became a folk hero , often compared to Robin Hood .
Jamini Bhushan Ray ( 1 July 1879 -- 11 August 1926 ) was an Indian physician , as well as an Ayurvedic doctor ( Kabiraj ) , an erudite Sanskrit scholar , and a philanthropist .
Célestin Lavigueur ( 19 January 1831 -- 11 December 1885 ) was a French Canadian musician and composer .
Major Sir Bruce Lovat Seton of Abercorn , 11th Baronet ( 29 May 1909 -- 28 September 1969 ) , better known as Bruce Seton , was a British actor and soldier .
Bertha of Aragon ( c. 1075 -- bef . 1111 ) was a Queen consort of Aragon and Navarre .
Li Rangyi ( 李讓夷 ) ( died 847 ? ) , courtesy name Daxin ( 達心 ) , was an official of the Chinese dynasty Tang Dynasty , serving as a chancellor during the reigns of Emperor Wuzong and ( briefly ) Emperor Wuzong 's uncle Emperor Xuānzong .
Ulrich II , Lord of Hanau ( c. 1280/1288 -- 23 September 1346 ) was Lord of Hanau from 1305/1306 until his death .
Daniel Gibson Harris ( 1915 - -2007 ) was an accountant , a British agent during World War II and a writer on Swedish naval history .
Douglas Frank Springhall ( 28 March 1901 -- 2 September 1953 ) , known as Dave Springhall , was a British communist activist .
Dorothea Palmer ( Ferguson ) ( born 1908 died 1992 ) was a Canadian who played a prominent role in the effort to legalize birth control in that country .
Feng Lun ( 568 - -627 ) , courtesy name Deyi , better known as Feng Deyi , formally Duke Miao of Mi ( 密繆公 ) , was an official of the Sui and Tang dynasties who served as a chancellor during the reigns of Emperor Gaozu of Tang and Emperor Taizong of Tang .
Lev Gillet ( born Louis Gillett ; 8 August 1893 - 29 March 1980 ) was an archimandrite of the Eastern Orthodox Church .
Nepomuceno de la Cerda ( 1752 - -1826 ) was a Spanish soldier of note , after whom the town of La Cerda , Texas , was named .
Paul Samson - Körner ( 13 November 1887 - 25 August 1942 ) was a German Heavyweight boxer .
Charles Malapert ( 1581 - -1630 ) was a Belgian Jesuit writer , astronomer and proponent of Aristotelian cosmology .
Gustavus Detlef Hinrichs ( 2 December 1836 -- 14 February 1923 ) was a chemist and natural philosopher most widely known for his findings on periodic laws within the chemical elements .
Harry Ware ( 22 October 1911 -- 28 October 1970 ) was an English footballer and manager .
Ghabdula Chelbir ( or only Chelbir ) was ruler of Volga Bulgaria from 1178 to 1225 .
Angus Hargreaves Robinson ( 22 July 1907 - 17 October 1973 ) was the owner of a grazing property , ' Yanjettee ' , at Coolup , Western Australia , as well as being an amateur ornithologist .
Joseph Hanks ( 1725 - -1793 ) was the great - grandfather of United States President Abraham Lincoln .
Hugh I'Anson Fausset ( 1895 - -1965 ) , was an English writer , a literary critic and biographer , and a poet and religious writer .
Waman Bapuji Metre ( वामण बापूजी मेत्रे ) ( 14 February 1906 -- 21 November 1970 ) , admiringly referred to as Dādā ( ' Elder Brother'in Bengali ) Metre in the Indian oil industry circles , was the doyen of Indian petroleum geologists .
Ira Lunan Ferguson , B.A. , B.Sc . , M.A. , M.Sc . , Ph.D. , LL.B. ( born Ira Lunan Lamontanio Ferguson , 1904 , died 1992 ) was an American psychologist and author of multiple autobiographies as well as several novels and many published essays and journal articles .
Manto Mavrogenous ( Greek : Μαντώ Μαυρογένους ) ( 1796 - July 1848 ) was a Greek heroine of the Greek War of Independence .
Peter Hooper ( 2 February 1933 -- 13 August 2011 ) was a professional footballer , who played for Bristol Rovers , Cardiff City and Bristol City in The Football League .
John Fountaine ( 1600 - -1671 ) was commissioner of the great seal of England from 1659 - 60 .
Major General Sir Henry Guy Riley KBE CB ( 1884 - -1964 ) was a senior British Army officer during the Second World War .
Sir William Dawes , 3rd Baronet PC ( 12 September 1671 - -30 April 1724 ) was an Anglican prelate .
Alan Oversby ( 20 February 1933 -- 8 May 1996 ) was one of the primary figures in the development of contemporary body piercing in Europe .
Michael Pacher ( c. 1435 -- August 1498 ) was an Austrian painter and sculptor from Tyrol active during the second half of the fifteenth century .
Charles Rowcroft ( 1798 , London -- 1856 ) , pastoralist and novelist , the son of Thomas Edward Rowcroft , a British consul in Peru .
Gérald Gagnier ( 14 October 1926 -- 14 January 1961 ) was a Canadian bandmaster , composer , and trumpeter .
Francisco Pelliza ( 1792 - 1879 ) was an Argentine military , patriot officer who fought in the Argentine War of Independence .
Orig Williams ( 20 March 1931 -- 12 November 2009 ) was a Welsh professional wrestler and wrestling promoter .
Max Graetz ( 1861 - 1936 ) was the President / CEO of the Ehrich & Graetz firm in Berlin .
August Querfurt ( 1696 - -1761 ) was an Austrian painter .
John Beaufort , 1st Duke of Somerset , KG ( 1403 -- 27 May 1444 ) was an English nobleman and military commander .
Kaspar , Count Palatine of Zweibrücken and Veldenz ( 11 July 1459 -- c. Summer 1527 ) was Duke of Zweibrücken from 1489 to 1490 .
August Klett ( Pseudonym : August Klotz ) ( 1866 in Heilbronn-1928 ) was a German schizophrenic outsider artist and one of the `` schizophrenic masters '' profiled by Hans Prinzhorn in his field - defining work Artistry of the Mentally Ill. The pseudonym August Klotz was given by Prinzhorn .
George Mackenzie , 2nd Earl of Seaforth ( died 1651 ) was a Highland clan chief and Scottish nobleman , who played an equivocating role in Scotland in the Wars of the Three Kingdoms .
Hugh Broughton ( 1549 -- 4 August 1612 ) was an English scholar and theologian .
Anne - Marie Krumpholtz ( née Steckler ; 1766 - -1813 ) was a French harpist and composer .
Yaakov ben Yakar ( 990 - -1064 ) was a German Talmudist .
Henry Corbet ( 31 December 1820 - 20 December 1878 ) was an English agricultural writer , and editor of the weekly The Mark Lane Express Agricultural Journal for twenty years .
Lawrence Dundas , 1st Earl of Zetland ( 10 April 1766 -- 19 February 1839 ) was a British politician and nobleman .
