David Záizar was a Mexican ranchera singer and actor who appeared in many Mexican films .
Dave Carter ( August 13 , 1952 -- July 19 , 2002 ) was an American folk singer - songwriter who described his style as `` post - modern mythic American folk music . ''
Antonio Farré ( born August 22 , 1961 ) is a Spanish actor , voice - over artist , and television host .
Adib Khan is an Australian novelist of Bangladeshi origin .
Charles Robinson , Jr. ( November 6 , 1829 - -July 30 , 1891 ) was a Massachusetts politician who served as the eighth mayor of Charlestown , Massachusetts .
Lee Wilkof ( born June 25 , 1951 ) is an American actor and veteran of the Broadway stage .
Christine Ohlman ( born November 25 , in the Bronx , New York City ) is a singer , songwriter , guitarist , recording artist , music scholar .
Francisco Marins , ( born November 23 , 1922 ) is a Brazilian writer .
Gail Katz is a film , television , and theatrical producer .
Charles Arnoldi , also known as Chuck Arnoldi and as Charles Arthur Arnoldi is an American painter , sculptor and printmaker .
Deepthi Kumara Gunarathne is a Sri Lankan activist , critic and politician .
Mayanti Langer is an Indian TV sports journalist with STAR .
Sir Henry Erskine , 5th Baronet ( ca . 1710 -- 7 August 1765 ) was a Scottish soldier and politician .
Prabhu Solomon ( Tamil : பிரபு சாலமன் ; born 7 May 1969 ) is an Indian film director who has primarily worked on Tamil films .
Gerardus Mes or Gherardus ( fl . c. 1561 ) was a Franco - Flemish composer .
Zane Buzby is an American actress , philanthropist , film director and television director .
Matthew Knight ( born c. 1994 ) is a Canadian actor who made his debut in 2002 when he played Peter in a television episode of Queer as Folk .
Robert Ladislas Derr is an American artist and educator born in the early 1970s .
Philip P. Mason is an American archivist and author , as well as the founding director of the Walter P. Reuther Library of Labor and Urban Affairs on the campus of Wayne State University in Detroit .
Warren Staley is the former chief executive officer of Cargill , Inc. of Minneapolis , Minnesota , USA .
Ivan Dawson , CBE was a British Virgin Islands politician .
Preben Maegaard ( born September 25 , 1935 ) , is a Danish renewable energy pioneer , author and expert .
Tench Coxe ( May 22 , 1755 -- July 17 , 1824 ) was an American political economist and a delegate for Pennsylvania to the Continental Congress in 1788 - 1789 .
A noted American poet , Anne Spencer was also a teacher , civil rights activist , librarian , and gardener .
Abraham Dimitri Rihbany known as Abraham Mitrie Rihbany ( Arabic : أبراهام متري الرحباني‎ , 1869 - 1944 ; sometimes spelled Rahbany ) was an American theologian , philologist and historian of Greek Orthodox Lebanese descent .
Boris Krajný is a Czech pianist , b. 1945 , best known for his work on Czech and French pianism - he was awarded the Académie Charles Cros 's 1982 Grand Prix du Disque for his recording of Albert Roussel , Arthur Honegger and Francis Poulenc piano concertos .
Grover Dale ( born July 22 , 1935 ) is an American actor , dancer , choreographer and theatre director .
John Wimpole or Wynpol , of Canterbury , Kent , was an English politician .
Tobias Ericsson ( born July 29 , 1987 in Stockholm ) is a Swedish professional ice hockey player ( left wing ) .
Holiday of My Lifetime is a documentary show for BBC One that began on 20 October 2014 and is hosted by Len Goodman .
Rhogogaster is a genus of sawflies in the family Tenthredinidae .
Fumonelix archeri ( syn . Mesodon archeri ) is a species of land snail in the family Polygyridae known commonly as Archer 's toothed land snail and Ocoee covert .
In plant systematics Apostasioideae is one of the five subfamilies recognised within the orchid family , Orchidaceae .
Praemordella martynovi is a species of beetle in the family Mordellidae , the only species in the genus Praemordella .
Phataria is a genus of sea stars in the family Ophidiasteridae from warmer parts of the East Pacific .
Neochryopus savagei is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Neochryopus .
Phrypeus rickseckeri is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Phrypeus .
Uloborus is a spider genus in the family Uloboridae with 72 described species .
Stixaceae is a family in the plant order Brassicales .
The Cape cormorant or Cape shag ( Phalacrocorax capensis ) is a bird endemic to the southwestern coasts of Africa .
Leschenault 's rousette ( Rousettus leschenaultii ) is a species of fruit bat .
The Xingu corydoras ( Corydoras xinguensis ) is a tropical freshwater fish belonging to the Corydoradinae sub - family of the Callichthyidae family .
Kirtland 's warbler ( Setophaga kirtlandii ) , also known as the jack pine warbler , is a small songbird of the New World warbler family ( Parulidae ) , named after Jared P. Kirtland , an Ohio doctor and amateur naturalist .
Eidocamptophallus chacei is a species of crab in the family Pseudothelphusidae , and the only species in the genus Eidocamptophallus .
John Dory , St Pierre or Peter 's Fish , refers to fish of the genus Zeus , especially Zeus faber , of widespread distribution .
Cyanomethia pseudothonalmus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Cyanomethia .
Sphaerocinidae is an extinct taxonomic family of fossil sea snails , sea butterflies , marine opisthobranch gastropod mollusks within the superfamily Cavolinioidea .
Malachius is a genus of soft - winged flower beetles belonging to the family Melyridae subfamily Malachiinae .
Neomysis ( from the Greek affix neo- , `` new '' , and the genus name Mysis ) is a genus of opossum shrimp ( mysid crustacean ) from the family Mysidae , distributed in the coastal zone of temperate seas of the Northern Hemisphere and South America .
Crocus kotschyanus , Kotschy 's crocus , is a species of flowering plant in the genus Crocus of the family Iridaceae , found from Turkey to Caucasus and Lebanon .
The family Messicobolidae is one of the smaller families of millipedes in the Order Spirobolida ( fewer than 30 described species ) .
The Berry Cave salamander ( Gyrinophilus gulolineatus ) is a species of salamander in the family Plethodontidae , endemic to the Ridge - and - Valley Appalachians of eastern Tennessee in the United States .
Vitalisia alternata is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae .
Metacorimus mroczkowskii is a species of beetle in the family Silvanidae , the only species in the genus Metacorimus .
Geoglobus is a hyperthermophilic member of the Archaeoglobaceae within the Euryarchaeota .
As a group within the sub - order Amblycera , lice within the family Menoponidae are still partially dependent on blood as a source of food and are therefore better able to be generalists .
Palaeotrachyderes laticornis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Palaeotrachyderes .
The African giant free - tailed bat ( Tadarida ventralis ) is a species of bat in the family Molossidae .
The Ansell 's shrew ( Crocidura ansellorum ) is a species of mammal in the family Soricidae .
Plectocomia is a genus of flowering plant in the Arecaceae family native to China , the Himalayas , and Southeast Asia .
The Bering wolffish ( Anarhichas orientalis ) is a marine fish in the family Anarhichadidae , the `` wolffish '' .
Despite their common name , Jerusalem crickets are not true crickets , as they belong to the family Stenopelmatidae , while true crickets belong to the family Gryllidae ; nor are they native to Jerusalem .
Leptofoenus is a genus of wasp in the family Pteromalidae , the type genus subfamily Leptofoeninae found in South , Central , and southern North America .
Protomeroleuca is a monotypic genus of moths of the Noctuidae family .
Megistostigma is a genus of plant of the family Euphorbiaceae first described as a genus in 1887 .
Acastoidea is a superfamily of trilobites from the order Phacopida , suborder Phacopina .
Oilea spinalis is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Oilea .
The Fujian niltava ( Niltava davidi ) is a species of bird in the Muscicapidae family .
Macromorphus boisduvali is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Macromorphus .
The Exopterygota , also known as Hemipterodea , are a superorder of insects of the subclass Pterygota in the infraclass Neoptera , in which the young resemble adults but have externally developing wings .
Montenegrina is a genus of air - breathing land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Clausiliidae , the door snails , all of which have a clausilium .
Ainsworthia is a genus of two species of plants in the Apiaceae family , all of which are endemic to Southwest Asia , Cyprus , and European Turkey .
Demonarosa is a genus of moths in the family Limacodidae from Asia .
Recent research shows that the genus Protosphyraena is not at all related to the true swordfish - family Xiphiidae , but belongs to the extinct family Pachycormidae .
The Kashmir flying squirrel ( Eoglaucomys fimbriatus ) is a species of rodent in the family Sciuridae .
Ceraptila was a genus of moths of the Noctuidae family , it is now considered to be a synonym of Rhynchina .
Picconia ( Picconia ) is a genus of two species flowering plants in the family Oleaceae .
Akebia is a genus of five species of flowering plant , within the family Lardizabalaceae .
Methanococcus is a genus of coccoid methanogens of the family Methanococcaceae .
The Anchieta 's sunbird ( Anthreptes anchietae ) is a species of bird in the Nectariniidae family .
The Philippine cobra ( Naja philippinensis ) also called northern Philippine cobra , is a stocky , highly venomous species of spitting cobra native to the northern regions of the Philippines .
The Panama hake ( Merluccius angustimanus ) is a merluccid hake of the genus Merluccius , found off the west coast of the Americas from Del Mar , California , to Ensenada de Tumaco , Colombia .
Odontobatrachus is a genus of frogs in the comprising the family Odontobatrachidae .
Hydatina is a genus of sea snails , bubble snails , marine opisthobranch gastropod mollusks in the family Aplustridae .
Cissus is a genus of approximately 350 species of woody vines in the grape family ( Vitaceae ) .
Cyathocrinus is an extinct genus of crinoids belonging to the family Cyathocrinitidae .
The New Zealand topknot , Notoclinus fenestratus , is a triplefin of the genus Notoclinus , found around the North Island of New Zealand in reef areas of broken rock and brown seaweed .
Uroplatus is a genus of geckos , commonly referred to as leaf - tail geckos , leaf - tailed geckos , or flat - tailed geckos , which are endemic to Madagascar and its coastal islands , such as Nosy Be .
Syrnolopsis is a genus of medium - sized freshwater snails with an operculum , aquatic gastropod mollusks in the family Paludomidae .
Etaballia dubia is a species of flowering plant in the legume family , Fabaceae .
Cotyachryson is a genus of round - necked longhorns beetle belonging to the family Cerambycidae , subfamily Cerambycinae .
The Leerfish , also Garrick ( Lichia amia ) is a species of marine fish in the Carangidae family , and is native to the Mediterranean and the coastal waters of western Africa to the coastal waters of eastern South Africa .
Dioon is a genus of cycads in the family Zamiaceae .
Spongilla is a genus of freshwater sponges in the family Spongillidae found in lakes and slow streams .
The Aran rock lizard ( Iberolacerta aranica ) is a species of lizard in the Lacertidae family .
The Transcaucasian water shrew ( Neomys teres ) is a species of mammal in the family Soricidae .
The subclass Euechinoidea includes almost all living species of sea urchin , and fossil forms going back as far as the Triassic .
The Planalto tapaculo ( Scytalopus pachecoi ) is a small passerine bird belonging to the genus Scytalopus , a genus of tapaculos .
Pelargonium line pattern virus ( PLPV ) is a plant pathogenic virus of the family Tombusviridae .
Aulacospermum is a genus of flowering plant in the Apiaceae , with 14 species .
Gaudryceratidae is a family belonging to the extinct ammonoid suborder Lytoceratina that lived from the Barremian of the Lower Cretaceous to the Maastrichtian of the Upper Cretaceous .
Chard ( Beta vulgaris subsp . vulgaris , Cicla - Group and Flavescens - Group ) is a leafy green vegetable often used in Mediterranean cooking .
Vitellariopsis is a group of plants in family Sapotaceae described as a genus in 1915 .
Helicophanta is a genus of air - breathing land snails , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropods mollusks in the family Acavidae .
The Sahamalaza sportive lemur ( Lepilemur sahamalazensis ) is a sportive lemur endemic to Madagascar .
Thorius , also known as minute salamanders , pigmy salamanders , or Mexican pigmy salamanders , is a genus of salamanders in the family Plethodontidae .
Fustiaria is a genus of scaphopods in the order Dentaliida and is the only genus comprising the family Fustiariidae , with 24 species .
Pachylemur remains were first described in 1895 by French zoologist Henri Filhol and were originally included in the genus Lemur , along with the ring - tailed lemur and other close relatives currently classified within the family Lemuridae .
Lithogenes is a genus of South American catfish ( order Siluriformes ) of the family Loricariidae .
Clavulinopsis is a genus of coral fungi in the Clavariaceae family .
Callipteridium is an extinct genus of pteridospermous seed ferns belonging to the family Cyclopteridaceae .
The Pomona roundleaf bat , Pomona leaf - nosed bat , or Andersen 's leaf - nosed bat ( Hipposideros pomona ) is a species of bat in the family Hipposideridae .
Finsch 's duck ( Chenonetta finschi ) was a large terrestrial species of duck formerly endemic to New Zealand .
Sudeticeratidae is one of nine families of the Pericyclaceae superfamily .
Secamonoideae is a subfamily of the dogbane family , Apocynaceae .
Battarreoides ( Battarraeoides is a variant spelling ) is a fungal genus in the family Agaricaceae .
The Acadian flycatcher ( Empidonax virescens ) is a small insect - eating bird of the tyrant flycatcher family .
Breynia is a plant genus in the family Phyllanthaceae , first described as a genus in 1776 .
The Brandt 's cormorant ( Phalacrocorax penicillatus ) is a strictly marine bird of the cormorant family of seabirds that inhabits the Pacific coast of North America .
Marstoniopsis is a genus of minute freshwater snails with a gill and an operculum , aquatic gastropod mollusks or micromollusks in the family Amnicolidae .
James ' sportive lemur ( Lepilemur jamesorum ) , or the Manombo sportive lemur , is a sportive lemur endemic to Madagascar .
Brown 's pademelon ( Thylogale browni ) is a species of marsupial in the family Macropodidae .
The Trocholitidae are Tarphycerida with whorls in close contact as with the Tarphyceratidae , but in which the siphuncle , similar in structure , becomes dorsal .
Heteraneflus castaneus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Heteraneflus .
Xylocopa violacea , the violet carpenter bee , is the common European species of carpenter bee , and one of the largest bees in Europe .
Annamocarya is a genus of flowering plants in the family Juglandaceae , containing only one species , Annamocarya sinensis , native to southwestern China ( Guangxi , Guizhou , Yunnan ) and northern Vietnam .
The Pacific oyster , Japanese oyster or Miyagi oyster ( Crassostrea gigas ) , is an oyster native to the Pacific coast of Asia .
Oncagnostus is a genus of trilobite in the order Agnostida , which existed in what is now Shandong , China .
The Southeast Asian shrew ( Crocidura fuliginosa ) is a species of mammal in the family Soricidae .
Tegeticula is a genus of moths of the Prodoxidae family , one of three genera known as yucca moths ; they are mutualistic pollinators of various Yucca species .
The Essex skipper ( Thymelicus lineola ) is a butterfly in family Hesperiidae .
The Dar es Salaam pipistrelle ( Pipistrellus permixtus ) is a species of vesper bat .
Conotrochus is a genus of small corals in the family Caryophylliidae .
Nattrassia is a genus of fungi in the family Botryosphaeriaceae for which there is the single species Nattrassia mangiferae .
Sivanesania is a genus of fungi in the family Botryosphaeriaceae for which there is the sole species Sivanesania rubi .
Actinella is a genus of land snails in the family Hygromiidae , the hairy snails and their allies .
The Lord Howe swamphen or white gallinule ( Porphyrio albus ) was a large bird in the family Rallidae endemic to Lord Howe Island , Australia .
Stomatellinae is a subfamily of small sea snails with a brilliantly nacreous interior of the shell , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Trochidae , the top snails .
The AEECL 's sportive lemur , Antafia sportive lemur or red - shouldered sportive lemur ( Lepilemur aeeclis ) is a sportive lemur endemic to Madagascar .
Platysphyrus tibialis is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Platysphyrus .
Cauarana iheringi is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Cauarana .
Poecilanthrax is a large , primarily Nearctic genus of flies belonging to the family Bombyliidae ( bee - flies ) .
Pleuroloba is a genus of small air - breathing land snails , terrestrial gastropod mollusks in the family Ellobiidae , the salt marsh snails .
Adelia is a genus of flowering plants in the spurge family , Euphorbiaceae , subfamily Acalyphoideae .
Hymenopyramis is a genus of plants in the Lamiaceae , first described in 1843 .
The Black - headed blenny ( Microlipophrys nigriceps ) is a species of combtooth blenny found in the Mediterranean Sea .
The Oruge tree frog ( Litoria modica ) is a species of frog in the Hylidae family .

The Perilampidae are a small family within the Chalcidoidea , composed mostly of hyperparasitoids .
Lepismatidae is a family of primitive wingless insects belonging to the order Thysanura with about 190 described species .
The Tamaulipas shiner ( Notropis braytoni ) is a small North American freshwater fish , living in the Rio Grande drainage in Texas and northern Mexico .
Celtis ehrenbergiana , called the desert hackberry or spiny hackberry , is a plant species that has long been called C. pallida by many authors , including in the `` Flora of North America '' database .
The Mediterranean moray ( sometimes also called Roman eel , Muraena helena ) is a fish of the moray eel family .
The Helena 's marsupial frog ( Gastrotheca helenae ) is a species of frog in the Hemiphractidae family .
The Arizona myotis ( Myotis occultus ) is a vesper bat species inhabiting much of the southwestern United States and central Mexico as far south as the Distrito Federal .
Clithon is a genus of freshwater snails or brackish snails that have an operculum , aquatic gastropod molluscs in the family Neritidae , the nerites .

Gould 's wattled bat ( Chalinolobus gouldii ) is a species of Australian wattled bat named after the English naturalist John Gould .
The Chilean jack mackerel ( Trachurus murphyi ) sometimes called the Inca scad , is a species of jack mackerel in the genus Trachurus of the family Carangidae .
Deltacoronaviruses are one of the four genera , alpha , beta , gamma , and delta in the subfamily Coronavirinae of the family Coronaviridae .
Pseudoseptis was a genus of moths that belongs to the Noctuidae family , it is now considered a synonym of Dichagyris .
Alloeomorphus formosus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Alloeomorphus .
The Sailfin snake - eel ( Letharchus rosenblatti , also known as the Black sailfin eel in Mexico ) is an eel in the family Ophichthidae ( worm / snake eels ) .
Phaulothamnus is a genus of plants formerly included in the family Phytolaccaceae but now considered a part of the Achatocarpaceae .
Cheilostomata ( accepted name Cheilostomatida ) , an order of Bryozoa in the class Gymnolaemata , are exclusively marine , colonial invertebrate animals .
The Goldspotted eel ( Myrichthys ocellatus , also known as the Goldspotted snake eel or the Dark - spotted snake eel ) is an eel in the family Ophichthidae ( worm / snake eels ) .
Argyrotaenia is a genus of moths the in the tribe Archipini within the family Tortricidae .
Holopyga fastuosa is a species of cuckoo wasps belonging to the family Chrysididae .
The Guianan warbling antbird ( Hypocnemis cantator ) is a species of bird in the family Thamnophilidae .
Ostracods , or ostracodes , are a class of the Crustacea ( class Ostracoda ) , sometimes known as seed shrimp .
Stein 's cuscus ( Phalanger vestitus ) is a species of marsupial in the family Phalangeridae .
Kalinowski 's mouse opossum or the Peru gracile mouse opossum ( Hyladelphys kalinowskii ) is a species of opossum in the family Didelphidae .

Apium virus Y ( AVY ) is a plant pathogenic virus in the genus Potyvirus and the virus family Potyviridae .
Ridley 's bat ( Myotis ridleyi ) is a species of vesper bat .
Rhodnius is a genus of assassin bugs in the subfamily Triatominae ( the kissing bugs ) , and is an important vector in the spread of Chagas disease .
Elrodoceras , which comes from the Middle Silurian of North America and Europe , is a late armenoceratid and , according to Curt Teichert , 1964 , a member of one of the two branches of the Armenoceratidae that also includes Armenoceras and Monocyrtoceras .
Apollonaster is a genus of abyssal sea stars in the family Goniasteridae .
The Hygrophoropsidaceae are a family of mushrooms that are gilled in appearance but lie within the Boletales .
The Antillean crested hummingbird ( Orthorhyncus cristatus ) is a species of hummingbird in the Trochilidae family .
The Greater Antillean elaenia ( Elaenia fallax ) is a species of bird in the Tyrannidae family .

In taxonomy , Bryopsis is a genus of marine green algae , specifically of the Bryopsidaceae .
Sleumerodendron is a monotypic genus of plant in the Proteaceae family .
Vandopsis , abbreviated as Vdps in horticultural trade , is a genus of orchids in family Orchidaceae .
Apoderus is a genus of leaf - rolling beetles belonging to the family Attelabidae subfamily Attelaninae .
Acteonella is a genus of extinct sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the extinct family Acteonellidae .
Heteromeryx is an extinct genus of Artiodactyla , of the family Protoceratidae , endemic to North America from the Eocene epoch ( Duchesnean to Chadronian stage ) 40.2 - -33.9 Ma , existing for approximately 6.3 million years .
Diplogyniidae is a family of parasitic mites belonging to the order Mesostigmata .
The Brandt 's mountain finch or black - headed mountain - finch ( Leucosticte brandti ) is a species of finch in the Fringillidae family .
Ankasocris is a genus of moths of the Zygaenidae family , containing only one species , Ankasocris striatus .
Sassafras is a genus of three extant and one extinct species of deciduous trees in the family Lauraceae , native to eastern North America and eastern Asia .
The Ugandan lowland shrew ( Crocidura selina ) is a species of mammal in the family Soricidae .
Dermatobranchus is a genus of sea slugs , or nudibranchs , marine gastropod molluscs in the family Arminidae .
The Umpqua chub ( Oregonichthys kalawatseti ) is a species of freshwater fish in the Cyprinidae family .
According to FishBase , they are part of the family Centriscidae , but some authorities split that family , in which case the genus Macroramphosus is in the family Macroramphosidae .

Linsleychroma monnei is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae ; the only species in the genus Linsleychroma .
The Bignose conger ( Rhynchoconger nitens , also known as the Needletail conger ) is an eel in the family Congridae ( conger / garden eels ) .
Cylindrobulla is the type genus of the family Cylindrobullidae and it is the only genus in the family .
Paracorophium is a genus of amphipods in the family Corophiidae .
Bucaniidae is an extinct family of paleozoic molluscs of uncertain position possibly being either Gastropods or Monoplacophorans in the superfamily Bellerophontoidea .
Neoclaviceps is a fungal genus of fungi in the family Clavicipitaceae .
Taxonomically , Homo is the only genus assigned to the subtribe Hominina which , with the subtribes Australopithecina and Panina , comprise the tribe Hominini ( see evolutionary tree below ) .
Xenodontinae is a subfamily of the Colubridae family of snakes .
The Shortfin lizardfish ( Saurida micropectoralis ) is a species of lizardfish that lives mainly off the coast of Japan .
Tangarona pensa is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Tangarona .
The Venezuelan flowerpiercer ( Diglossa venezuelensis ) is a species of bird in the family Thraupidae .
The Greenbrier cavesnail , scientific name Fontigens turritella , is a species of very small or minute freshwater snail with an operculum , an aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Hydrobiidae .
Saururus is a genus of plants in the family Saururaceae containing two species .
The Australian brushturkey or Australian brush - turkey ( Alectura lathami ) , also frequently called the scrub turkey or bush turkey , is a common , widespread species of mound - building bird from the family Megapodiidae found in eastern Australia from Far North Queensland to Illawarra in New South Wales .
Wegelina is a genus of funguy in the family Calosphaeriaceae containing 7 species .
Felis margarita margarita is a subspecies of the sand cat , inhabiting the Sahara .
The Australian water dragon ( Intellagama lesueurii , formerly Physignathus lesueurii ) , which includes the eastern water dragon ( I. l. lesueurii ) and the Gippsland water dragon ( I. l. howittii ) subspecies , is an arboreal agamid species native to eastern Australia from Victoria northwards to Queensland .
The Javan spitting cobra ( Naja sputatrix ) also called the southern Indonesian cobra , or Indonesian cobra , is a stocky and highly venomous species of spitting cobra native to Indonesia .
The Chiapan climbing rat ( Tylomys bullaris ) is a species of rodent in the family Cricetidae .
Chlorion is a genus of Hymenoptera of the Sphecidae family of wasps .
The Nicobar long - tailed macaque ( Macaca fascicularis umbrosa , popularly known as the Nicobar monkey ) is a subspecies of the crab - eating macaque ( M. fascicularis ) , endemic to the Nicobar Islands in the Bay of Bengal .
Chlopsis is a genus of eels of the family Chlopsidae .
Zeuneria is a genus of katydids crickets in family Phaneropteridae subfamily Phaneropterinae .
Lanelater is a genus of click beetle belonging to the family Elateridae .
Pauridia is a flowering plant genus in the family Hypoxidaceae , endemic to South Africa .
Macrophoma is a genus of anamorphic fungi in the family Botryosphaeriaceae .
Copiphana was a genus of moths of the Noctuidae family , it is now considered a synonym of Teinoptera .
Wainuia is a genus of air - breathing predatory land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod molluscs in the family Rhytididae .
Dermestes is a genus of beetles in the family Dermestidae , the skin beetles .
The Malagasy sheldgoose ( Centrornis majori ) is an extinct monotypic species of large goose in the shelduck subfamily .
The Doucet 's musk shrew ( Crocidura douceti ) is a species of mammal in the family Soricidae .
Leucospermum ( Pincushion , Pincushion Protea or Leucospermum ) is a genus of about 50 species of flowering plants in the family Proteaceae , native to Zimbabwe and South Africa , where they occupy a variety of habitats , including scrub , forest , and mountain slopes .
Mimagoniatites is a genus of ammonoid cephalopod which lived during the early Devonian , regarded as belonging to the Agoniatitdae as a member of the subfamily Mimagoniatitinae .
Saussure 's shrew ( Sorex saussurei ) is a species of mammal in the family Soricidae .
Anopla are a class of marine worms of the phylum Nemertea , characterized by the absence of stylets on the proboscis , the mouth being below or behind the brain , and by having separate openings for the mouth and proboscis .
Furcifer angeli , also known as Angel 's chameleon , initially described as Chamaeleo angeli , is a species of chameleon that is endemic to northwest Madagascar .
Byrsonima is one of about 75 genera in the Malpighiaceae , a family of flowering plants in the order Malpighiales .
Heliothinae is a small subfamily of moths in the family Noctuidae .
The Kimberley froglet , Crinia fimbriata , is an Australian froglet found on the Mitchell Plateau in the north - west region of the Kimberley Mountains in Western Australia .
Ivantstov & Fedonkin ( 2002 ) , suggest that Rugoconites may possess tri - radial symmetry and be a member of the Trilobozoa .
Barberetta is a genus of herbs in the family Haemodoraceae , first described as a genus in 1868 .
The Continental Divide tree frog , Isthmohyla graceae , is a species of frog in the Hylidae family found in Panama and possibly Costa Rica .
Phylogenetic analyses place Barasaurus within the Owenettidae , the sister taxon of Procolophonidae .
The Spanish algyroides ( Algyroides marchi ) , also commonly known as the Spanish keeled lizard or Valverde 's lizard , is a species of lizard in the family Lacertidae .
Luetzelburgia ( common names include sucupira and angelim ) is a genus of flowering plants in the legume family , Fabaceae .
Bittium is a genus of very small sea snails , marine gastropod molluscs in the family Cerithiidae , the horn snails .
Palmulacypraea is a genus of sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Cypraeidae , the cowries
Cabrera 's hutia ( Mesocapromys angelcabrerai ) is a species of rodent in the family Capromyidae .
Prevost 's ground sparrow ( Melozone biarcuatum ) , also known as the white - faced ground sparrow , is an American sparrow .
Palaeonictis is an extinct hyena - like predatory mammal belonging to the family Oxyaenidae , existing from the late Paleocene to the early Eocene times .
Anacoracidae is an extinct shark family in the order Lamniformes .
Trichilogaster is a small genus of chalcid wasps in the family Pteromalidae , subfamily Ormocerinae .
Carlowrightia is a genus of flowering plants in the bear 's breeches family , Acanthaceae .
Dodecastigma is a genus of plants under the family Euphorbiaceae first described as a genus in 1932 .
The Kashmir flycatcher ( Ficedula subrubra ) is a small passerine bird in the flycatcher family Muscicapidae .
The Guadalupe caracara ( Caracara lutosa ) or mourning caracara is an extinct bird of prey belonging to the falcon family ( Falconidae ) .
Levinellidae is a family of sponges in the order Clathrinida .
Thalassoceratidae a family of late Paleozoic ammonites included in the goniatitid superfamily Thalassoceratoidea along with the Bisatoceratidae .
Lewin 's rail ( Lewinia pectoralis ) is a species of bird in the family Rallidae .
The Basilan flying squirrel ( Philippines flying squirrel or Mindanao flying squirrel ) ( Petinomys crinitus ) is a species of rodent in the family Sciuridae .
Exema is a genus of leaf beetles in the tribe Chlamisini .
The seamoths make up a family of fishes , the Pegasidae , within the order Gasterosteiformes .
Micropterix is a genus of small primitive metallic moths in the insect order Lepidoptera within the family Micropterigidae that is distributed across Europe south to North Africa and east as far as Japan .
The Natal ghost frog ( Hadromophryne natalensis ) is a species of frog in the Heleophrynidae family .
The Asian gray shrew ( Crocidura attenuata ) is a species of mammal in the family Soricidae .
Ctenothrissa is a prehistoric genus of ray - finned fish in the supposed order `` Ctenothrissiformes '' .
The Japanese whiting , Sillago japonica , ( also known as the Japanese sillago or Shiro - gisu ) is a common species of coastal marine fish belonging to the smelt - whiting family , Sillaginidae .
The Nevis skink , Oligosoma toka , is a nationally vulnerable species of skink native to New Zealand .
The Gulf menhaden ( Brevoortia patronus ) is a small marine filter feeding fish belonging to the family Clupeidae .
Theraphosinae is a large subfamily of Mygalomorphae spiders in the Theraphosidae family found if the Neotropical ecozone .
Within Massospondylidae , Leyesaurus was found to be most closely related to Adeopapposaurus .
Vieira 's titi monkey ( Callicebus vieirai ) is a species of titi , a type of New World monkey , from central - northern Brazil .

The Guinean weever ( Trachinus armatus ) is a fish of the Trachinidae family , widespread in the eastern Atlantic along the coasts of Africa from Mauritania to Angola .
Proatriplex is a monotypic plant genus in the subfamily Chenopodioideae of the Amaranthaceae family , with the only species Proatriplex pleiantha ( Syn . Atriplex pleiantha ) .
Berlanguella is a genus of sea slugs , specifically dorid nudibranchs , shell - less marine gastropod molluscs in the family Chromodorididae .
The Limacinidae are a family of small sea snails , pteropods , pelagic marine gastropod mollusks in the clade Thecosomata ( sea butterflies ) .
Scolosanthus is a genus of flowering plants in the coffee family , Rubiaceae .
Pseudolecanactis is a lichenized genus of fungi in the family Roccellaceae ; according to the 2007 Outline of Ascomycota , the placement in this family is uncertain .
The Milkweed Leaf Beetle ( Latin : Labidomera clivicollis ) is a species of Beetle from the family Chrysomelidae .
Myrmeanthrenus frontalis is a species of beetle in the family Dermestidae , the only species in the genus Myrmeanthrenus .
Lenophyllum is a genus of flowering plants in the orpine family , Crassulaceae .
Saukiella is a genus of trilobite of the Saukiidae family .
Trigonias is an extinct genus of rhinoceros from the late Eocene ( Chadronian ) some 35 million years ago of North America ( Prothero , 2005 ) .
Stenopsocidae is a family of Psocoptera belonging to the suborder Psocomorpha , in the infraorder Caeciliusetae .
Sisyrinchieae is the second largest tribe in the Iridoideae subfamily .
Monterissa is a genus of minute cave snails with an operculum , gastropod mollusks in the family Hydrocenidae .
Siphopatella walshi ( Syn . Crepidula walshi ) , common name : the Eastern White Slipper Limpet , is a species of small sea snail , a slipper snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Calyptraeidae , the slipper snails or slipper limpets , cup - and - saucer snails , and Chinese hat snails .
The Kano mole ( Mogera kanoana ) is a species of mole native to Taiwan .

Sericomyia is a genus of large Hoverflies , from the family Syrphidae , in the order Diptera .
Titanites is an extinct ammonite cephalopod genus within the family Dorsoplanitidae , that lived during the upper Tithonian stage of the Late Jurassic .
Dalodesmidae is a family of millipedes in the order Polydesmida , containing at least 250 species found in the Southern Hemisphere .

Safflower ( Carthamus tinctorius L. ) is a highly branched , herbaceous , thistle - like annual plant .
Paragehyra is a genus of lizards in the family Gekkonidae ( geckos ) .
The Chinese cobra ( Naja atra ) , also called Taiwan cobra , is a species of cobra in the Elapidae family , found mostly in southern China and a couple of neighboring nations and islands .
Marstonia scalariformis , previously known as Pyrgulopsis scalariformis , common name the moss pyrg , is a species of freshwater snail with a gill and an operculum , aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Hydrobiidae .
Ornithomyinae is a subfamily of the fly family Hippoboscidae .
Boulenger 's pipe snake , Cylindrophis boulengeri , is a species of nonvenomous snake in the Cylindrophiidae family endemic to Indonesia .
The Indian roundleaf bat ( Hipposideros lankadiva ) is a species of bat in the family Hipposideridae .
Woosnam 's broad - headed mouse or Woosnam 's zelotomys ( Zelotomys woosnami ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .

Aplectrum hyemale is a species of orchid in the family Orchidaceae native to the eastern United States and Canada , from Oklahoma east to the Carolinas and north to Minnesota , Ontario , Quebec and Massachusetts .
The American butterfish ( also known as the Atlantic butterfish ) , Peprilus triacanthus , is a butterfish of the family Stromateidae .

Allotrioceras is a tubular fossil from the Middle Ordovician of the state of New York , collected by Rousseau H. Flower ; included by him in the Endocerida and placed in a new family , the Allotrioceratidae .
Winnipegoceras is included in the discosorid family Westonoceratidae and is derived from Westonoceras .
Eoacanthocephala is a class of parasitic worms , within the phylum Acanthocephala .
Hoffmann 's woodpecker , Melanerpes hoffmannii , is a resident breeding bird from southern Honduras south to Costa Rica .

Cleonus is a weevil genus in the family Curculionidae .
Botryosphaeria stevensii is a plant pathogen that causes cankers on several tree species including apple as well as black dead arm on grape .
Orthocycloceras is an extinct genus of actively mobile carnivorous cephalopod , essentially a Nautiloid , that lived in what would be Europe during the Silurian to Devonian from 428.2 - -412.3 mya , existing for approximately 15.9 million years .
Zhuchengceratops is a genus of extinct leptoceratopsid ceratopsian that lived during the Upper Cretaceous of modern - day China .
Frasera coloradensis is a species of flowering plant in the gentian family known by the common names Colorado green gentian , or Colorado gentian , and Colorado frasera .
Modiolarca impacta is a species of saltwater clam , a mussel , a marine bivalve mollusk in the family Mytilidae , the mussels .
Bolbena hottentotta , common name hottentot mantis , is a species of praying mantis found in Angola , Kenya , and Namibia .
Apypema yara is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Apypema .
Three distinct species of the family 's sole genus , Aulostomus , are described .
Sisyrinchium halophilum is a species of flowering plant in the iris family known by the common name Nevada blue - eyed grass .
Olive snails , also known as olive shells and olives , scientific name Olividae , are a taxonomic family of medium to large predatory sea snails with smooth , shiny , elongated oval - shaped shells .
Xystodesmidae is a family of millipedes .
Wakinosaurus ( meaning `` Wakino lizard '' ) is a genus of theropod dinosaur from the Early Cretaceous ( Hauterivian - Barremian ) Sengoku Formation of Kyushu , Japan .
Helladia humeralis is a species of longhorn beetle in the Lamiinae subfamily that can be found in Iran , Turkey and Near East .
Psittacinae is a subfamily of Afrotropical or Old World parrots ; the eleven species are found in two genera .
Sedum sexangulare , also known as tasteless stonecrop , is a species of succulent perennial and evergreen plant of the genus Sedum .
It contains only one species , Praescobura chrysomaculata , which is found in northern Vietnam .
Hyparrhenia is a genus of grasses .
Herina ghilianii is a species of ulidiid or picture - winged fly in the genus Herina of the family Ulidiidae found in Italy , Malta , and Morocco .
Paspalidium ( watercrown grass ) is a genus of tropical and subtropical plants in the grass family .

Rasboroides vaterifloris , known as the pearly rasbora , vateria flower rasbora or fire rasbora , is a species of freshwater cyprinid fish endemic to Sri Lanka .

It contains only one species , Arnia nervosalis , which is found in France , Spain , Portugal and on Corsica , Sardinia and Sicily , as well as in North Africa , including Algeria and Morocco .

The Xiphydriidae are a family of wood wasps with the distinct characteristic of having globose heads borne on their long , skinny `` necks '' ; they are also unusual in the habit of boring into dead wood , rather than living trees .
Sepiola aurantiaca , also known as the Golden Bobtail , is a rare species of bobtail squid native to the northeastern Atlantic Ocean .

The Chatham tomtit ( Petroica macrocephala chathamensis ) is a subspecies of tomtit found on some of the smaller islands of New Zealand .
The Honduran small - eared shrew ( Cryptotis hondurensis ) is a species of mammal in the family Soricidae .
Hylorina sylvatica ( also known as the Emerald forest frog , or in Spanish , sapo arboreo ) is a species of frog in the Batrachylidae family .
Equidae ( sometimes known as the horse family ) is the taxonomic family of horses and related animals , including the extant horses , donkeys , and zebras , and many other species known only from fossils .
Chuanchia labiosa is a species of cyprinid fish that is only found in the upper reaches of the Yellow River in China .
The genus is monotypic , containing the single species Tholurna dissimilis .
Gilia leptantha is a species of flowering plant in the phlox family known by the common name fineflower gilia .
The Restionaceae , also called restiads and restios , are a family of perennial , evergreen rush - like flowering plants native to the Southern Hemisphere ; they vary from 10 cm to 3 m in height .
Ecrobia truncata , common name the truncated marsh hydrobia or minute hydrobia , is a species of very small aquatic snail , an operculate gastropod mollusk in the family Hydrobiidae .
Vitiaziella cubiceps is a species of flabby whalefish known from the Kuril - Kamchatka Trench and the South China Sea at depths of from 1,500 to 6,200 metres ( 4,900 to 20,300 ft ) .
Disa cardinalis is a species of orchid found in South Africa ( S. Cape Prov . - Riversdale ) .
Hesperoyucca newberryi is a plant species endemic to Arizona .
Phoenicocoris obscurellus is a species of plant bugs belonging to the family Miridae , subfamily Phylinae that is found throughout continental Europe and the British Isles , except for southeastern Europe .
Pustularia childreni , common name the children 's cowrie , is a species of sea snail , a cowry , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Cypraeidae , the cowries .
Myennis octopunctata is a species of picture - winged fly in the genus Myennis of the family Ulidiidae .
The water voles are large voles in the genus Arvicola .
Discinisca is a genus of brachiopod with fossils dating back to the Early Devonian to the Pliocene of Africa , Europe , North America , and New Zealand .
Larinus obtusus is a species of true weevil known as the blunt knapweed flower weevil .
Zhylgaia is a genus of birds known only from fossils .
Dinilysia ( meaning `` terrible ilysia '' ) is an extinct genus of snake from the Late Cretaceous ( Coniacian ) of South America .
Iris uniflora is a species in the genus Iris , it is also in the subgenus of Limniris .
Flacourtia indica ( syn . Flacourtia ramontchi ) , known commonly as ramontchi , governor 's plum , batoko plum , Pachnala and Indian plum ( বৈঁচি ) , is a species of flowering plant native to much of Africa and tropical and temperate parts of Asia .
Verbascum virgatum , commonly known as twiggy mullein and wand mullein , is a plant species in the family Scrophulariaceae .
Eudibamus is an extinct genus of biped bolosaurid ankyramorph parareptile known from the Free State of Thuringia of central Germany .
Conophytum flavum is a small South African species of succulent plant of the genus Conophytum .
Englerophytum is a group of trees in the Sapotaceae described as a genus in 1914 .
Penicillium thymicola is a halotolerant species of the genus of Penicillium which produces okaramine A , daldinin D , alantrypinone , seranttrypinone , fumiquinazoline F and fumiquinazoline G.
Callianassidae is a family of ghost shrimp of the order Decapoda .
Alopecosa accentuata is a species of wolf spider found commonly in open habitats throughout continental Europe .
Tillandsia caput - medusae is a species of flowering plant in the bromeliad family , Bromeliaceae , subfamily Tillandsioideae .
Conus iodostoma , common name the violet - mouth cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
Myosotella denticulata , common name the `` mouse ear snail '' , is a European species of small , salt marsh snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Ellobiidae .
Chattonella is a genus of marine raphidophytes associated with red tides .
Discaria pubescens ( Hairy Anchor Plant or Australian Anchor Plant ) is a species of flowering plant in the family Rhamnaceae .
Harpalus salinus is a species of ground beetle native to Europe , where it can be found in Ukraine and southern part of Russia .
Orobanche vallicola is a species of broomrape known by the common name hillside broomrape .
Stigmatogobius sadanundio is a species of goby native to south Asia from India to Indonesia including Sri Lanka and the Andaman Islands .
Glikmanius is an extinct genus of shark which lived in the Carboniferous of North America and Russia .
Micronycteris is a genus of leaf - nosed bats .
Porcelain crabs are decapod crustaceans in the widespread family Porcellanidae , which superficially resemble true crabs .
Oreochromis is a large genus of tilapiine cichlids , fishes endemic to Africa and the Middle East .
Nostoc commune is a species of cyanobacterium in the family Nostocaceae .
Sashatherina giganteus is a species of freshwater silverside endemic to Lake Lakama in West Papua , Indonesia .
Hydriastele is a diverse and widespread genus of flowering plant in the palm family found throughout Australia and New Zealand , Melanesia , Polynesia , and Southeast Asia .
Anematichthys armatus is a species of freshwater cyprinid native to Southeast Asia .
Xenopoma is a genus of land snails with an operculum , terrestrial gastropod mollusks in the family Pomatiidae .
Acropora acuminata is a species of acroporid coral found in Australia , the Red Sea , the central Indo - Pacific , Japan , the northern Indian Ocean , the East China Sea , southeast Asia , and the western Pacific Ocean .
Ranunculus auricomus , known as goldilocks buttercup or Greeenland buttercup , is a perennial species of buttercup native to Eurasia .
The bird genus Balearica ( also called the crowned cranes ) contains two extant species in the crane family Gruidae : the black crowned crane ( B. pavonina ) and the grey crowned crane ( B. regulorum ) .
Hagenomyia is a genus of antlions ( Myrmeleontidae ) containing around 20 species occurring in Eastern Asia , tropical Africa , and Australia .
Pardosa pseudostrigillata is a wolf spider species in the genus Pardosa found in Austria , Italy and Slovenia .
Bolma henica , common name the deep sea star shell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Turbinidae , the turban snails .
Quesnelia testudo ( tess - too'do ) is a species of bromeliad in the genus Quesnelia .
Neotyphodium chilense is a species of fungus in the Clavicipitaceae family .
Euphyes berryi , known as Berry 's skipper , is a rare species of butterfly of the Hesperiidae family , historically found in wet areas from North Carolina to Florida .
Cryptocentrum is a neotropical genus of orchid that grows as far north as Nicaragua and south to Bolivia , with twenty species known to date .
Petrorhagia dubia is a species of flowering plant in the pink family known by the common name hairy pink .
Annachlamys flabellata is a species of scallop , a marine bivalve mollusc in the family Pectinidae .
Rossiinae is a subfamily of bobtail squid encompassing four genera and around twenty species .
Apachyidae is a small family of earwigs , in the suborder Forficulina and the order Dermaptera .
Bloomeria clevelandii is a rare species of flowering plant that is known by the common name San Diego goldenstar .
Montia howellii is a species of flowering plant in the purslane family known by the common names Howell 's miner 's lettuce and Howell 's montia .
Cyttomimus is a genus of zeniontid fishes native to the Pacific Ocean .
Notogomphus maathaiae , commonly known as Maathai 's longleg , is a species of dragonfly in the clubtail family Gomphidae .
Hemiemblemaria simulus , the Wrasse blenny , is a species of chaenopsid blenny found in coral reefs in the western Atlantic ocean .
Lythrum californicum is a species of flowering plant in the loosestrife family known by the common name California loosestrife .
The Antarctic petrel is the only known species in the genus Thalassoica , and is a member of the Procellariidae family , and the Procellariiformes order .
Arion intermedius is a species of land slug in the family Arionidae , the roundback slugs .
Hemichromis frempongi is a species of fish in the cichlid family .
Ceanothus maritimus , with the common name maritime ceanothus , is a species of shrub in the buckthorn family Rhamnaceae .
Tachypleus tridentatus , commonly known as the Chinese , Japanese or tri - spine horseshoe crab , is a species of horseshoe crab found in the seas off China , Indonesia , Japan , South Korea , Malaysia , the Philippines , Taiwan , and Vietnam .
Selenicereus hamatus is a species of Cactaceae and produce one of the largest flowers in the family .

Metanephrops challengeri ( commonly known as the New Zealand lobster or New Zealand scampi ) is a species of slim , pink lobster that lives around the coast of New Zealand .
Pseudomugil gertrudae , commonly known as the spotted blue - eye , is a species of fish in the family Pseudomugilidae .
Acanthoibidion chevrolatii is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Acanthoibidion .
Hydrangea integrifolia is a species of Hydrangea , native to Taiwan and the Philippines at elevations above 8,000 ft . ( 2,400 m. ) .
Geophis is a genus of colubrid snakes that belong to the Xenodontinae subfamily and are typically referred to as Latin American earth snakes ( Spanish : culebra minera or culebra minadora ) .
Athous caviformis is a species of brown - coloured click beetle from Elateridae family which can be found in Hungary , Croatia , and Bosnia and Herzegovina .
Ctenocephalides is a flea genus in the tribe Archaeopsyllini .
Clavaria is a genus of fungi in the family Clavariaceae .
Brumus is a genus of beetle of the Coccinellidae family .
Escobaria minima ( syn . Coryphantha minima ) is a rare species of cactus known by the common names Nellie cory cactus , Nellie 's pincushion cactus , birdfoot cactus , and others .
Carparachne is a genus of huntsman spiders found in Namibia .
Carpolestes simpsoni is an extinct species of Plesiadapiformes , which is one of the earliest primate - like mammals appearing in the fossil record during the late Paleocene .
Euryxaenapta rondoni is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Euryxaenapta .
Oryza sativa , commonly known as Asian rice , is the plant species most commonly referred to in English as rice .
Anadara is a genus of saltwater bivalves , ark clams , in the family Arcidae .
†Harmogenanina linophora was a species of air - breathing land snails or semislugs , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Helicarionidae .
The genus Albionbaatar was named by Kielan - Jaworowska Z. and Ensom P.C. in 1994 based on a single species .
Linaria purpurea is a species of flowering plant in the plantain family known by the common name purple toadflax .
Drechslera is a genus of fungi .
Centrodoras brachiatus is a species of thorny catfish found in the Amazon basin of Brazil , Colombia and Peru .
Janthina exigua , also known as the dwarf janthina , is a species of small holoplanktonic sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Janthinidae , the violet snails or purple storm snails .
Solen marginatus , common name Grooved Razor Shell , is a species of marine bivalves in the family Solenidae .
Vegetia ducalis , the ducal princeling , is a species of moth in the family Saturniidae .
Ficedula beijingnica is a species of flycatcher observed in China .
Zetela alphonsi is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Solariellidae , the top snails .
Margarites giganteus , common name the giant margarite , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Margaritidae .
Prestoea is a genus of palms native to the Caribbean , Central and South America .
Birulia kishinouyei is a shrimp species in the genus Birulia .
Senna domingensis is a flowering plant species in the legume family ( Fabaceae ) .
Montia chamissoi is a species of flowering plant in the purslane family known by the common names of water minerslettuce , water montia , Indian lettuce , and toad lily .
Chrysanthemum morifolium ( also known as Florist 's daisy and Hardy garden mum ) is a species of perennial plant from Asteraceae family .
Primula sikkimensis ( Himalayan cowslip , Sikkim cowslip , Chinese : 鍾花報春 ; pinyin : zhōng huā bàochūn ) is a species of flowering plant in the family Primulaceae , native to the Himalayan region at altitudes of 3,200 - -4,400 m ( 10,499 - -14,436 ft ) , from western Nepal to south west China .
Uraspis uraspis is a species of jack in the family Carangidae .
Harttia novalimensis is a species of armored catfish endemic to Brazil where it is found in the Das Velhas River basin .

Galium bermudense , the Bermuda bedstraw , is a plant species in the Rubiaceae .
Psathyrophlyctis is a genus of fungi in the order Ostropales .
Pelagosaurus ( meaning `` lizard of the open sea '' ) is an extinct genus of thalattosuchian crocodyliform that lived during the Toarcian stage of the Lower Jurassic , around 183 Ma to 175 Ma ( million years ago ) , in shallow epicontinental seas that covered much of what is now Western Europe .
Ampelocissus elegans is a species in the genus Ampelocissus .
Streptomyces anandii is a bacterium species from the genus of Streptomyces which has been isolated from soil from in the region of Al - Taif in Saudi Arabia .
Dypsis humilis is a rare species of stemless palm that was discovered in Madagascar in 2007 by a collaboration between botanists from Madagascar and Royal Botanical Gardens , Kew .
Microcavia ( mountain cavies ) is a genus of rodents in the family Caviidae .
Periptychidae is a family of Paleocene placental mammals , known definitively only from North America .
Priolepis aureoviridis , the Yellow - green goby , is a species of goby native to the central Pacific Ocean where it is known to occur in Micronesia , Johnston Atoll and the Hawaiian Islands .
Heteronyx queenlandicus is a beetle species that was first described in 1909 .
Heterophotus ophistoma , the Wingfin snaggletooth , is a species of barbeled dragonfish found in oceans world wide at depths of 790 to 1,420 metres ( 2,590 to 4,660 ft ) .
Maubeugia is a genus of traversodontid cynodont from the Late Triassic of France .
The priapum fishes are a family , Phallostethidae , of atheriniform fish native to freshwater and brackish habitats in southeast Asia .
Flufftails ( genus Sarothrura ) are small birds related to rails and finfoots .
Dolichoderus brevipennis is an extinct species of ant in the genus Dolichoderus .
Mahonia monyulensis is a shrub in the Berberidaceae first described as a species in 1961 .
Oeceoclades , collectively known as the monk orchids , is a genus of flowering plants from the orchid family , Orchidaceae .
Oenothera primiveris is a species of flowering plant in the evening primrose family known by the common name desert evening primrose .
Psammathodoxa cochlidioides is a species of moth in the family Erebidae .
Helianthus deserticola , the desert sunflower , is a plant species native to Arizona , Nevada and Utah .
Stylidium perplexum is a species of triggerplant that is endemic to south - west Western Australia .
Carabus trichothorax is a species of black - coloured ground beetle in the Carabinae subfamily that is endemic to Sichuan , China .
Panulirus is a genus of spiny lobsters in the family Palinuridae , including those species which have long flagella on their first antennae .
Dipterocarpus costulatus is a species of tree in the family Dipterocarpaceae found in Malaysia ( peninsular Malaysia and Sarawak ) and Indonesia ( Sumatra and Kalimantan ) .
Tarascosaurus ( `` Tarasque lizard '' ) is a genus of , perhaps abelisaurid , theropod dinosaur from Late Cretaceous of France .
Raorchestes ochlandrae ( Ochlandrae reed frog ) is a species of shrub frog in the Rhacophoridae family .
Sericornis is a genus of small , mainly insectivorous , birds , the scrubwrens .
The Lacertidae are the family of the wall lizards , true lizards , or sometimes simply lacertas , which are native to Europe , Africa , and Asia .
Megacephala cruciata is a species of ground beetle in the subfamily of Carabinae that was described by Brulle in 1837 .
Chaenodraco wilsoni , the Spiny Icefish , is a species of crocodile icefish native to the Southern Ocean where it occurs at depths of from 200 to 800 metres ( 660 to 2,620 ft ) .
Carabus smaragdinus is a species of beetle belonging to the family Carabidae .
Plectronocerida is a primitive order from which subsequent cephalopod orders are ultimately derived .
Tropheus is a small genus of six species of cichlids endemic to Lake Tanganyika in East Africa .
Prionosciadium watsonii is a plant species known from the Mexican states of Durango and Sinaloa .
Schizothorax is a genus of cyprinid fish from Central and East Asia .
Acanthotretella is a genus of brachiopod known from the Burgess Shale .
Stephopoma roseum is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Siliquariidae , the slit worm snails .
Streptomyces guanduensis is a acidophilic bacterium species from the genus of Streptomyceswhich has been isolated from pine forest soil from Guandu in the Yunnan Province in China .

Aloysia citrodora is a species of flowering plant in the verbena family Verbenaceae , native to western South America .

Dicrastylis is a genus of plants in the Lamiaceae , first described in 1855 .
Moratia cerifera is a species of palm tree endemic to New Caledonia , and the only species in the genus Moratia .
Typhlocaris ayyaloni is a species of troglobitic shrimp in the family Typhlocarididae .
Atherinops affinis , the topsmelt silverside or simply topsmelt , is a species of Neotropical silverside native to the eastern Pacific Ocean .
Erythrolamprus ocellatus , commonly known as the Tobago false coral , is a species of colubrid snake , which is endemic to the island of Tobago ( in the Republic of Trinidad and Tobago ) .
Gwyneddosaurus is an extinct genus of aquatic tanystropheid reptile .
Oedipina maritima ( common name : maritime worm salamander ) is a species of salamander in the family Plethodontidae .
The New Zealand pea crab lives most commonly in green - lipped mussels ( Perna canaliculus ) , but can also be found in many other bivalve molluscs including the blue mussel ( Mytilus edulis aoteanus ) , the Pacific oyster ( Crassostrea gigas ) and a species of clam ( Chione stutchburyi ) .
Neblinichthys pilosus is a species of armored catfish endemic to Venezuela where it is found in the upper Negro , Casiquiare and Baria River basins .
Calibanus is a genus of two species of flowering plants , both evergreen succulents from dry areas of northeastern Mexico .
†Zygitidae is an extinct family of fossil sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the clade Vetigastropoda ( according to the taxonomy of the Gastropoda by Bouchet & Rocroi , 2005 ) .
Haliotis squamosa , common name the squamose abalone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Haliotidae , the abalones .
Edgarosaurus is a genus of polycotylid plesiosaur , containing one species , E. muddi .
Carabus obsoletus is a species of black - coloured beetle from Carabidae family , that can be found in Czech Republic , Hungary , Moldova , Romania , Slovakia , Ukraine .

Haplochromis dichrourus is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Victoria , but has not been seen since 1986 .
Epilobium obcordatum is a species of perennial plant in the primrose family ( Onagraceae ) , known by the common name rockfringe willowherb and rock fringe .
Eremothera refracta is a species of evening primrose known by the common name narrowleaf suncup .
Batheulima abbreviata is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the genus Batheulima , a minor genus within the family Eulimidae .
Cheilopogon pinnatibarbatus japonicus , is a subspecies of flyingfish of the family Exocoetidae , found in the seas around Japan .
Polymastiidae is a family of demosponges found in oceans throughout the world .

Gastrochilus obliquus is a species of orchid native to China , the Himalayas and Southeast Asia .

Paraceratherium is an extinct genus of hornless rhinoceros , and one of the largest terrestrial mammals that has ever existed .

Salmophasia boopis , the boopis razorbelly minnow , is a species of cyprinid fish in the genus Salmophasia .
Lonchodytes is a Late Cretaceous genus of aquatic bird , which lived along the shores of the Western Interior Seaway .
Stegnosperma is a genus of flowering plants , consisting of three species of woody plants , native to the Caribbean , Central America , and the Sonoran Desert .
Delphinium grandiflorum is a species of Delphinium known by the common name Siberian larkspur .
Thomasomys is a genus of rodent in the family Cricetidae , named after British zoologist Oldfield Thomas .
Solidago curtisii , commonly called Curtis ' goldenrod and mountain decumbent goldenrod , is a North American species of flowering plants in the sunflower family .
Artamidae is a family of passerine birds found in Australia , the Indo - Pacific region , and Southern Asia .

Erannis is a geometer moth genus of the subfamily Ennominae .
The Draconettidae , slope dragonets , are a small family ( about 14 species ) of fish in the order Perciformes .
Nicrophorus argutor is a species of burying beetle found in Russia , Mongolia , China and Kazakhstan .
Petropedetes perreti is a species of frog in the Petropedetidae family endemic to Cameroon .
Callionymus platycephalus is a species of dragonet endemic to the Pacific waters around the Philippines where it occurs from the surface to 48 metres ( 157 ft ) .
Myriophyllum alterniflorum , known as alternate water - milfoil or alternateflower watermilfoil , is a species of water - milfoil .
Haplochromis cyaneus is a species of cichlid endemic to the Tanzanian part of Lake Victoria .
Psilocybe caeruleoannulata is a species of psilocybin mushroom found in Uruguay and Brazil , where it grows on marshy grounds , grasslands , or pastures .
Richardia scabra , commonly called rough Mexican clover or Florida pusley , is a species of flowering plant in the coffee family .
The African wildcat ( Felis silvestris lybica ) , also called Near Eastern wildcat is a wildcat subspecies that lives in Africa and around the periphery of the Arabian Peninsula .
Lepraria is a genus of leprose crustose lichens that grows on its substrate like patches of granular , caked up , mealy dust grains .
Hyparrhenia filipendula is a species of perennial bunchgrass commonly known as fine thatching grass and fine hood grass .
This genus was named by Andrew T. McDonald and John R. Horner in 2010 , and the type species is Rubeosaurus ovatus .
Trachinus is a genus of weevers , order Perciformes that consists of seven extant species .
Before the introduction of exotic fish species including the Eastern mosquitofish and trout to Australian waterways the Australian grayling and spotted galaxias were keenly fished by recreational anglers using fly - fishing gear .
Thalassopterus zancleus is a species of swimming sea slug , a shell - less pelagic marine opisthobranch gastropod mollusk in the family Clionidae .
Hymenocallis tubiflora is a plant species from Trinidad and northern South America .
Recilia raoi is a species of bug from the Cicadellidae family , that is endemic to India .
Curcuma zanthorrhiza , known as Temulawak , Java ginger or Javanese ginger , is a plant species , belonging to the ginger family .
Buniapone is a monotypic genus of ants in the subfamily Ponerinae .
Phasianella variegata , common name the variegated pheasant , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Phasianellidae .
Mitra mitra , common name the Episcopal miter , is a species of large predatory sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Mitridae , the miters .
The Phlebovirus genus currently comprises over 70 antigenically distinct serotypes , only a few of which have been studied .
Conus mitratus , common name the mitred cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
Cyrtopodion elongatum , the Yangihissar gecko , is a lizard species in the genus Cyrtopodion .
Qiliania ( from the Xiongnu qilian , `` heaven '' ) is an extinct genus of early bird from the lower Cretaceous ( Aptian stage ) about 120 million years ago .
Gibbohammus stricticollis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Gibbohammus .
Melanella baldra is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Eulimidae .
Lophogobius is a genus of gobies native to the Pacific and western Atlantic oceans .
Paranaleptes reticulata , known commonly as the Cashew Stem Girdler , is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae .
Agriomyia is a genus of wasp in the order Hymenoptera .
Mordellistena aethiops is a species of beetle in the family Mordellidae discovered in 1882 .
Ceanothus sonomensis , with the common name Sonoma ceanothus , is a rare species of shrub in the buckthorn family Rhamnaceae .
It was described by Watson in 1975 and contains the single species Aphyarctia surinamensis , which is found in French Guiana , Surinam , Ecuador and Bolivia .
Gastromyzon contractus is a species of river loach in the genus Gastromyzon .
The genus contains one species , Divarctia diva , from Central Asia .
Banksieaeformis is a genus that encompasses plant species only known from fossil leaves that can be attributed to the Proteaceae tribe Banksieae , but can not be attributed to an extant ( living ) genus .
Zhouornis is an extinct genus of enantiornithine dinosaur known from the Early Cretaceous Jehol Group ( Aptian stage ) of western Liaoning Province , northeastern China .
Hylesia nigricans is a species of lepidoptera of the Saturniidae family .
Anomiopus parallelus is a species of true dung beetle that can be found in northern Brazil and French Guiana , and can be found in the Amazon and cerrado biomes .
Lamprima micardi is a species of beetle in the Family Lucanidae , that is found in Western Australia .
Carrierea calycina is a species of tree in the willow family .
Cambarus chasmodactylus , commonly called the New River Crayfish , is a species of crayfish endemic to the New River drainage system
Adinauclea is a monospecific genus of flowering plants in the Rubiaceae family .
Pseudoclyzomedus ohbayashii is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Pseudoclyzomedus .
Ephedra lomatolepis is a species of Ephedra that is native to Kazakhstan and to the Tuva region of Siberia .
Eotitanops ( ' dawn titan - face ' ) is an extinct genus of brontothere native to North America and Asia .
Dorsetisaurus is a genus of extinct lizard from the Early Cretaceous ( Berriasian ) Purbeck Group of Durlston Bay , in Dorset .
Alcmonacaris winkleri is an extinct species of shrimp in its own genus , Alcmonacaris , which can not yet be placed in a family .
It contains only one species , Plaesiostola diaplintha , which is found on Borneo .
Drosophila sharpi ( syn . D. attigua ) is a rare species of fly , one of several species known as the Hawaiian picture - wing flies .
Micropterocerus longifacies is a species of ulidiid or picture - winged fly in the genus Micropterocerus of the family Ulidiidae .
Hymenopappus tenuifolius , the Chalk Hill hymenopappus , is a North American species of flowering plant in the daisy family .
Piper marginatum , the cake bush , Anesi wiwiri , marigold pepper , Ti Bombé in Creole or Hinojo , is a plant species in the genus Piper found in moist , shady spots in the Amazon rainforest in Surinam , French Guiana and Brazil .
The Zeiformes are a small order of marine ray - finned fishes most notable for the dories , a group of common food fish .
Bangaloides strandi is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Bangaloides .
Papilio xanthopleura is a species of swallowtail butterfly from the genus Papilio that is found in Peru and Brazil .
Camissonia pubens is a species of evening primrose known by the common name hairy suncup .
Trachelipus pierantonii is a species of woodlouse in the genus Trachelipus belonging to the family Trachelipodidae that can be found in Trento , Italy .
Penthorum chinense is a plant species native to much of East Asia .
Philodromus medius is a spider species found in Europe ( Greece , Cyprus ) and Asia ( Israel , Azerbaijan ) .
Symphoricarpos longiflorus is a species of flowering plant in the honeysuckle family known by the common names desert snowberry and fragrant snowberry .
Antennaria aromatica ( scented pussytoes ) is a North American species of plants in the sunflower family .
Stygobromus lucifugus is an extinct species of amphipod crustacean in the family Crangonyctidae .
Pholas dactylus or common piddock is a bioluminescent clam - like species of marine mollusc found on the coasts of the North Atlantic and the Mediterranean Sea .
Allium calyptratum is a plant species found in Israel , Syria , Palestine and Turkey .
Yunnanilus paludosus is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Yunnanilus .
Minicrania ( `` small skull '' ) is an extinct genus of tiny antiarch fish , with armor averaging up to about 2 centimetres ( 0.79 in ) long , which lived during the Lochkovian epoch in Early Devonian Yunnan Province , China and northern Vietnam .
Heteroteuthis hawaiiensis is a species of bobtail squid native to the central and western Pacific Ocean .
Pteraspidomorphi is an extinct class of early jawless fish .
Blepharidachne is a small genus of New World plants in the grass family , generally knwn as eyelashgrass or desertgrass .
The Dacrymycetes are a class consisting of only one family of jelly fungi , which has imperforate parenthesomes and basidia that are usually branched .
Sagartia ichthystoma is a species of sea anemone in the family Sagartiidae , also known as the fish - mouth anemone .
Populus euphratica , commonly known as the Euphrates poplar or desert poplar , is a species of poplar tree in the willow family .
Lepidiolamprologus attenuatus is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Tanganyika preferring areas with sandy substrates in which it digs crater - shaped nests .
Trionyx kansaiensis is an extinct species of softshell turtle uncovered from the Late Cretaceous of Tajikistan and Qyzylorda , Kazakhstan .
Anise is a food plant for the larvae of some Lepidoptera species ( butterflies and moths ) , including the lime - speck pug and wormwood pug .
Luidia magnifica , the magnificent star , is a species of starfish in the family Luidiidae .
Chorizanthe corrugata is a species of flowering plant in the buckwheat family known by the common name wrinkled spineflower .
Ixora brevipedunculata is a species of flowering plant in the Rubiaceae family .

Oxycera fallenii , the Irish major , is a European species of soldier fly .
Scobinancistrus is a genus of armored catfishes native to the southeastern Amazon Basin in Brazil .
Pachydactylus boehmei is a species of thick - toed gecko belonging to the Pachydactylus weberi group , found in Namibia .
The Karner blue ( Lycaeides melissa samuelis ) is an endangered subspecies of small blue butterfly which was once found in significant numbers in the Miller Beach community of the Indiana Dunes National Park .
Lupinus tracyi is a species of lupine known by the common name Tracy 's lupine .
Sabal palmetto , also known as cabbage palm , palmetto , cabbage palmetto , palmetto palm , blue palmetto , Carolina palmetto , common palmetto , swamp cabbage and sabal palm , is one of 15 species of palmetto palm ( Arecaceae , genus Sabal ) .
Tasmanipatus anophthalmus is a species of invertebrate in the Peripatopsidae family .
Westonoceras is an extinct nautiloid genus from the Discosorida that lived during the Middle and Late Ordovician that has been found in North America , Greenland , and Northern Europe .
Perulibatrachus is a genus of toadfishes known from the Indian and Atlantic Oceans .
Pseudolmedia is a flowering plant genus in the mulberry family ( Moraceae ) .
Panulirus marginatus is a species of spiny lobster in the family Palinuridae which is endemic to the Hawaiian Islands .
Xenophoridae , commonly called carrier shells , is a family of medium - sized to large sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the clade Littorinimorpha .

Lycophidion variegatum , also known as the variegated wolf snake , is a species of small nocturnal snake in the family Lamprophiidae .

Porcellio novus is a species of woodlouse in the genus Porcellio belonging to the family Porcellionidae that can be found in Portugal and Spain .
Ophiomorus raithmai is a species of skink endemic to India and Pakistan .

Oreocereus is a genus of cacti ( family Cactaceae ) , known only from high altitudes of the Andes .

Labeobarbus osseensis is a species of cyprinid fish which is endemic to Ethiopia .
Amaurobius hercegovinensis is a spider species found in Bosnia and Herzegovina .

Baeometra is a genus in the family Colchicaceae containing a single species , Baeometra uniflora .
Genevievella is a genus of trilobite with an short inverted egg - shaped outline , a wide headshield , small eyes , and long genal spines .
The family contains the single genus Atractogloea , which in turn contains the single species Atractogloea stillata , found in the USA .

Orodrominae is a subfamily of Thescelosaurid Ornithopod dinosaurs from the Cretaceous of North America .
Nelson 's kangaroo rat ( Dipodomys nelsoni ) is a species of rodent in the family Heteromyidae which is endemic to the central plateau of Mexico .
Uca annulipes is a species of fiddler crab found along the coastline from South Africa to Somalia , Madagascar , India , China , Indonesia , Malaysia and the Philippines .

Bradybaenidae is a taxonomic family of medium - sized to small land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the superfamily Helicoidea .
Cornus alba ( red - barked , white or Siberian dogwood ) is a species of flowering plant in the family Cornaceae , native to Siberia , northern China and Korea .
