Asterionella is a genus of pennate freshwater diatoms .
Diploschistes ( crater lichen ) is a genus of crustose lichens with a thick , cracked ( areolate ) body ( thallus ) with worldwide distribution .
The Imbricate Bulbophyllum ( Bulbophyllum imbricatum ) is a species of orchid .
Anabaraspis is a genus of redlichiid trilobite .
Leptosiphon nudatus ( syn . Linanthus nudatus ) is a species of flowering plant in the phlox family known by the common name Tehachapi linanthus .
The Yunnan lar gibbon ( Hylobates lar yunnanensis ) , also known as the Yunnan white - handed gibbon , is a subspecies of the lar gibbon , a primate in the gibbon family , Hylobatidae .
Cyrioides australis , commonly known as the dark blue banksia jewel beetle , is a species of beetle in the family Buprestidae native to southeastern Australia .
Plectritis is a genus of plants in the honeysuckle family .
Jamesoniella undulifolia , the marsh flapwort , or marsh earwort , is a species of liverwort in the Jungermanniaceae family .
Hedychrum nobile is a species of cuckoo wasp ( the family Chrysididae ) .
Alcyna kingensis , common name the King Island kelp shell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Trochidae , the top snails .
Naarda ivelona is a species of moth in the family Noctuidae from Madagascar .
Conus figulinus , common name the fig cone , is a cone snail , a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
Myrica rivas - martinezii is a species of plant in the Myricaceae family .
Castanea pumila , commonly known as the Allegheny chinquapin , American chinquapin ( from the Powhatan ) or dwarf chestnut , is a species of chestnut native to the eastern United States from southern New Jersey and Pennsylvania south to central Florida , west to eastern Texas , and north to southern Missouri and Kentucky .
Pachyhalictus bedanus is a species of bees in the genus Pachyhalictus , of the family Halictidae .
Gallardosaurus is a genus of pliosaurid plesiosaur from the Caribbean seaway .
Caeciliidae is the family of common caecilians .
Phyrganeoidea , the giant caddisfly superfamily , may be paraphyletic with Limnephiloidea .
Sepia trygonina , the trident cuttlefish , is a species of cuttlefish in the genus Sepia from the Red Sea and the western Indian Ocean .
Araucaria muelleri is a species of conifer in the Araucariaceae family .
Euphorbia punicea is a species of euphorb commonly known as Jamaican poinsettia .
Acer glabrum is a species of maple native to western North America , from southeastern Alaska , British Columbia and western Alberta , east to western Nebraska , and south through Washington , Oregon , Idaho , Montana and Colorado to California , Arizona and New Mexico .
Eosuchians are an extinct order of diapsid reptiles .
Zatheria is a group ( sublegion ) of mammals that includes the common ancestor of Arguitheriidae , Arguimuridae , Vincelestidae , Peramuridae and Tribosphenida ( living therians plus all of its ancestors ) .
Nebria simulator is a species of ground beetle in the Nebriinae subfamily that is endemic to North Korea .
Phlaocyon minor is an extinct species of canid mammal known from the Miocene - Oligocene ( Arikareean NALMA , more than 20 million years ago ) of the United States ( Wyoming , South Dakota , Nebraska , Wyoming , and Texas . )
Pratapa is a genus of butterfly in the family Lycaenidae . The members ( species ) of this genus are found in the Far Eastern Palearctic ecozone ( China ) and in the Indomalaya ecozone .
Leucactinia is a genus of flowering plants in the marigold tribe within the sunflower family .
Vateria indica , the white dammar , is a species of plant in the Dipterocarpaceae family .
Mimhoplomelas diadelioides is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Mimhoplomelas .
Vexillum crocatum , common name : the saffron mitre , is a species of small sea snail , marine gastropod mollusk in the family Costellariidae , the ribbed miters .
Calliostoma ornatum , common name the ornate topshell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Calliostomatidae .
Pseudophilautus rugatus was a species of frog in the Rhacophoridae family .
Aparallactus jacksonii , or Jackson 's centipede - eater , is a species of venomous rear - fanged snake in the family Atractaspididae .
Hyptis alata ( musky mint , or clustered bushmint ) is a shrub species of flowering plant in the Lamiaceae , the mint family .
Osmorhiza brachypoda is a species of flowering plant in the carrot family known by the common name California sweetcicely .
Telescopus semiannulatus , commonly known as the tiger snake , tiger cat snake , or striped cat snake is a species of colubrid snake .
Eolepidopterigoidea is an extinct superfamily of moths , containing the single family Eolepidopterigidae , although the genus Undopterix is sometimes placed in a separate family Undopterigidae .
Rhinophis dorsimaculatus , commonly known as the polka - dot earth snake , is a species of snake in the Uropeltidae family .
Astianthus is a monotypic genus of flowering plants in the Bignoniaceae family .
Hollandaea riparia , sometimes named Roaring Meg Hollandaea , is a species of Australian rainforest small trees , constituting part of the plant family Proteaceae .
Lathyrus sphaericus is a species of wild pea known by the common names grass pea and round - seeded vetchling .
Lymania globosa is a species in the genus Lymania .
Nemegtomaia ( `` Nemegt mother '' ) is a genus of oviraptorid dinosaur from the late Cretaceous Period of what is now Mongolia .
Echinocactus horizonthalonius is a species of cactus known by several common names , including devilshead , turk 's head cactus , blue barrel cactus , eagle 's claw , horse maimer , horse crippler , and visnaga meloncillo .
The pike icefish , Champsocephalus esox , is a species of icefish found at depths of 50 - -250 m ( 160 - -820 ft ) in the oceans off Patagonia , the Falklands and South Georgia .
Holothuria leucospilota , commonly known as the black sea cucumber , is a species of marine invertebrate in the family Holothuriidae .
Gobitrichinotus is a genus of sand darters , with one species from rivers in Madagascar and another from coastal waters ( salt , brackish and fresh ) of the western Pacific Ocean .
Caesalpinia sappan is a species of flowering tree in the legume family , Fabaceae , that is native to Southeast Asia and the Malay archipelago .
Tropaeolum asplundii is a species of plant in the Tropaeolaceae family .
Heuchera merriamii is a species of flowering plant in the saxifrage family known by the common name Merriam 's alumroot .
Acanthaspis siva is a species of assassin bug .
Caluromyinae is a subfamily of opossums .
It contains only one species , Dacgleia cerata , which is found in Vietnam .
Thaumatomastix is a Rhizaria genus .
Thelidomus aspera is a species of air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Pleurodontidae .
Stefania satelles ( Spanish : Rana Stefania Del Aprada - tepuy ) is a species of frog in the family Hemiphractidae .
Verbesina virginica , the white crownbeard , is a species of flowering plant in the aster family .
Hypopygus is a genus of bluntnose knifefishes native to northern South America .
Acsala is a genus of lichen moths in the family Erebidae .
Melica frutescens , woody melicgrass , is a species of grass in the Poaceae family that can be found in such US states as Arizona and California and in Mexico .
Suillus pseudoalbivelatus is a species of bolete fungus in the Suillaceae family .
Ceropegia candelabrum is a plant species from the subfamily Asclepiadoideae .
The species Pseudomonas riboflavina was transfer to Devosia riboflavina
Parastrigulia africana is a species of beetle in the family Buprestidae , the only species in the genus Parastrigulia .
Solariella micraulax , common name the fine - groove solarelle , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Solariellidae .
Leontopodium coreanum is a species of plant in the Asteraceae family .
Centotheceae is a small tribe of grasses with six species in two genera , distributed in Africa and Asia .
Paraponera clavata is a species of ant , commonly known as the bullet ant , named on account of its powerful and potent sting due to its venom .
Heterodactylus is a genus of gymnophthalmid lizards endemic to Brazil .
Bourreria velutina is a species of plant in the family Boraginaceae .
Xanthoceras sorbifolium ( yellowhorn , shiny leaf yellowhorn , goldenhorn , Chinese flowering chestnut ) is a woody perennial in the soapberry family , Sapindaceae , and the only species in the genus Xanthoceras .
Taruga longinasus ( common names : southern whipping frog , long - snouted tree - frog ) is a species of frog in the Rhacophoridae family .
Lycodon osmanhilli , commonly known as the Colombo wolf snake , is a species of colubrid snake , which is endemic to Sri Lanka .
Lithospermum incisum is a species of flowering plant in the borage family known by several common names , including narrowleaf stoneseed , fringed gromwell , narrowleaf puccoon , and plains stoneseed .
Ruellia simplex ( Britton 's wild petunia , Mexican petunia , Mexican bluebell ) is a species of flowering plant in the acanthus family , Acanthaceae .
Theba pisana , common names the white garden snail , sand hill snail , white Italian snail , Mediterranean coastal snail , and simply just the Mediterranean snail , is an edible species of medium - sized , air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Helicidae , the typical snails .
Athamanta turbith is a species of flowering plant in the Apiaceae .
Vitis heyneana is a species of climbing vine in the grape family endemic to Asia .
Adelotypa bolena is a species of butterfly in the Riodinidae family .
Psilocybe medullosa is a species of psychoactive mushroom .
Chanaresuchus is an extinct genus of proterochampsian archosauriform .
Conus canonicus , common name the tiger cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
Camptoceras hirasei is a species of air - breathing freshwater snails with sinistral shells , aquatic pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Planorbidae .
Howea belmoreana , the curly palm , kentia palm , or Belmore sentry palm , is a species of flowering plant in the family Arecaceae , endemic to Lord Howe Island , Australia .
Leptophilypnion is a genus of small sleeper gobies endemic to the Amazon Basin in South America .
Rafflesia philippensis is a parasitic plant species of the genus Rafflesia that was named by Blanco in his Flora de Filipinas in 1845 .
Allium teretifolium is a plant species native to Xinjiang , Kazakhstan and Kyrgyzstan .
Donax vittatus , or the banded wedge shell , is a species of bivalve mollusc in the order Veneroida .
Calliclinus nudiventris is a species of labrisomid blenny endemic to the Pacific coast of Chile .
Lancetilla del Páramo ( Castilleja pumila ) is a flowering species of plant in the Orobanchaceae family .
Trichilogaster acaciaelongifoliae is a species of Australian chalcid wasps that parasitises , among others , Acacia longifolia ( long - leaved wattle , or Sydney golden wattle ) , which has become an invasive pest in several countries .
Cochlespira radiata , common name the common star turret , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Cochlespiridae .
Hemiscorpiidae is a family of scorpions with 72 described species in 12 genera .
Fritillaria viridea is a rare species of flowering plant in the lily family known by the common name San Benito fritillary .
Callicarpa ampla , also called the capa rose , is a species of plant in the Verbenaceae family .
Diaptomus is a genus of copepods with a single eye spot .
Griphotherion is an extinct genus of notoungulate mammal from the Eocene of Argentina .
Paraphago rostratus is a species of distichodontid fish endemic to the Democratic Republic of Congo .
Naziritor zhobensis , the Zhobi mahseer , is a species of cyprinid fish endemic to Pakistan .
†Libera tumuloides was a species of small air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusc in the family Endodontidae .
Muhlenbergia porteri is a species of grass known by the common names bush muhly and Porter 's muhly .
Hylaeochampsa is an extinct genus of eusuchian crocodylomorph .
Bathysciadium costulatum is a species of sea snail , deep - sea limpet , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Bathysciadiidae .
Temnocephala lamothei is a species of flatworm in the family Temnocephalidae .
Termitaradus dominicanus is an extinct species of termite bug in the family Termitaphididae known from a Miocene fossil found on Hispaniola .
Terebra guttata , common name the eyed auger , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Terebridae , the auger snails .
Paragraciella schoudeteni is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Paragraciella .
Strobilurus tenacellus , commonly known as the pinecone cap , is a species of agaric fungus in the family Physalacriaceae .
Clathrina cordata is a species of sponge in the genus Clathrina from South Africa .
Amblyomma americanum , or lone star tick , is a species of tick in the genus Amblyomma .
Catharia is a monotypic genus of moths , containing the single species Catharia prenealis .
The Lago Blanco tuco - tuco ( Ctenomys fodax ) is a species of rodent in the family Ctenomyidae .
Vanilla raabii is a species of orchid in the Vanilla genus .
Pholidotrope is a genus of mostly small deep water sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Chilodontidae .
Cyperus grayoides is a species of sedge known by the common names Illinois flatsedge and Mohlenbrock 's umbrella sedge .
Ericameria cuneata is a species of flowering shrub in the daisy family known by the common name cliff goldenbush .
Kennedia coccinea ( coral vine ) is a species of flowering plant in the family Fabaceae , endemic to the south - west of Western Australia .
Contusus is a genus of pufferfishes native to the coastal waters of southern Australia and New Zealand .
Hornungia is a small genus of plants in the mustard family .
Dermatobranchus glaber is a species of sea slug , a nudibranch , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Arminidae .
Leccinum insigne , commonly known as the aspen bolete or the aspen scaber stalk , is a species of bolete fungus in the family Boletaceae .
Ctenochaetus hawaiiensis ( commonly known as chevron tang , but also known as black surgeonfish , Hawaiian bristletooth , Hawaiian kole or Hawaiian surgeonfish ) are a species of reef surgeonfish in the family Acanthuridae .
Antirrhinum virga ( syn . Sairocarpus virga ) is a species of New World snapdragon known by the common name tall snapdragon .
Telmatochromis dhonti is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Tanganyika where it prefers rocky substrates .
Idotea granulosa is a species of marine isopod in the family Idoteidae .
Hypleurochilus multifilis , the Featherduster blenny , is a species of combtooth blenny found in the western Atlantic ocean , around Texas , USA .
Paddlefish ( family Polyodontidae ) are basal Chondrostean ray - finned fish .
Horezmia is an extinct Mesozoic genus of prehistoric salamanders .
Nyssodesmus python also known as the python millipede or large forest - floor millipede is a species of flat - backed millipede of the family Platyrhacidae commonly found in Costa Rica , where it occurs widely and is locally abundant in the Caribbean slopes from sea level to around 365 meters ( 1,200 feet ) in elevation .
Lepidurus arcticus is a species of tadpole shrimp which inhabits both ephemeral pools and permanent freshwater lakes of Norway , Greenland , Finland , Sweden , Svalbard , Iceland , Russia and the Kuril Islands .
The genus Legionella is a pathogenic group of Gram - negative bacteria that includes the species L. pneumophila , causing legionellosis ( all illnesses caused by Legionella ) including a pneumonia - type illness called Legionnaires ' disease and a mild flu - like illness called Pontiac fever .
Spencer 's goanna or Spencer 's monitor ( Varanus spenceri ) is a species of monitor lizards native to the Barkly region in central Queensland / Northern Territory , Australia .
Luvaris necopinatus is a species of extinct louvar that lived in the Tethys Ocean during the early Paleogene .
Deinonychus ( /daɪˈnɒnᵻkəs/ dy - NON - i - kəs ; Greek : δεινός , ' terrible ' and ὄνυξ , genitive ὄνυχος ' claw ' ) is a genus of carnivorous dromaeosaurid coelurosaurian dinosaurs , with one described species , Deinonychus antirrhopus .
Rhytida meesoni is a species of small , air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusc in the family Rhytididae .
Lespedeza leptostachya is a rare species of flowering plant in the legume family known by the common names prairie lespedeza and prairie bush - clover .
Saprinus ornatus is a species of clown beetles belonging to the family Histeridae .
Arthrochilus , commonly called elbow orchids , is a genus of flowering plants from the orchid family , Orchidaceae .
The Savalai hairtail , Lepturacanthus savala , also known as Small - head hairtail , is a species of snapper native to the Indian Ocean and into the west Pacific Ocean as far east as Australia .
Lasioderma serricorne , commonly known as the cigarette beetle , cigar beetle , or tobacco beetle , is an insect very similar in appearance to the drugstore beetle ( Stegobium paniceum ) and the common furniture beetle ( Anobium punctatum ) , and all three species belong to the family Anobiidae .
Hoplocorypha narocana is a species of praying mantis found in Ethiopia , Kenya , Tanzania , Chad , and Zambia .
Parrotiopsis is a genus of deciduous shrub or small tree in the witch hazel family .
Ilanga illustris is a species of very small sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Solariellidae .
Cumulopuntia is a genus of cactus ( family Cactaceae ) .
The Ceram mangrove monitor , Varanus cerambonensis , is a species of monitor lizards found in Indonesia .
Larinus is a genus of true weevils , comprising about 180 species , mostly in the Palaearctic region .
Leptodirus hochenwartii , or L. hohenwarti , is a cave beetle in the family Leiodidae and the only species in the genus Leptodirus .
Trifolium barbigerum is a species of clover known by the common name bearded clover .
Fucus radicans is a species of brown algae in the family Fucaceae , endemic to and recently evolved within the Baltic Sea .
Chiropsalmus quadrigatus is a species of box jellyfish in the Chiropsalmidae family and can be found in the waters around Malaysia .
Prodajus ostendensis is a species of marine isopod in the family Dajidae and is found in the North Sea .
Treponema is a genus of spiral - shaped bacteria .
Echiniscoides sigismundi is the type species of Echiniscoides the oldest genus of tardigrades .
Squalogadus modificatus , the Tadpole whiptail , is a species of rattail found in the Atlantic and Pacific Oceans where it occurs at depths of from 600 to 1,740 metres ( 1,970 to 5,710 ft ) .
Sicyopterus is a genus of gobies native fresh waters from Madagascar to the Pacific islands .
Aporrhais pesgallinae is a species of medium - sized sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Aporrhaidae , the pelican 's foot snails or pelican 's foot shells .
Loweriella boltoni is a species of ant and is the only known species of genus Loweriella .
Anhydrophryne is a genus of frogs in the Pyxicephalidae family , formerly in Petropedetidae .
Esomus is a genus comprising the Flying Barbs .
Esperiana daudebartii is a species of a freshwater snail with an operculum , an aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Melanopsidae .
Traccatichthys is a genus of stone loaches from southern China and Vietnam .
Arnica dealbata is a species of Californian plants in the tarweed tribe within the aster family The species is known by the common name mock leopardbane .
Allium simillimum , the Simil Onion , or dwarf onion , is a plant species native to Idaho and Montana ( Gallatin and Ravalli Counties ) .
The sole species is Herpolirion novae - zelandiae , commonly known as Sky Lily .
Lavigeria paucicostata is a species of tropical freshwater snail with a gill and an operculum , aquatic gastropod mollusc in the family Paludomidae .
Pycnogonidae is a family of sea spiders .
Trachycephalus lepidus is a species of frog in the Hylidae family endemic to Brazil .
Helicarion mastersi is a species of air - breathing land snail , also referred to as a semi - slug because of its small shell .
Dendrelaphis is a genus of colubrid snakes , distributed from Pakistan , India and southern China to Indonesia , Timor - Leste , the Philippines , Australia , New Guinea and the Solomon Islands .
Homogalax is an extinct genus of tapir - like herbivore .
Sargassum pallidum is a species of seaweed native to East Asia and Southeast Asia .
Paradistichodus dimidiatus is a species of distichodontid fish that occurs in the African nations of Burkina Faso , Cameroon , Chad , Gambia , Ghana , Guinea , Guinea - Bissau , Mali , Mauritania , Niger , Nigeria , and Senegal .
Pteroplius acuminatus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Pteroplius .
Gelechioidea ( from the type genus Gelechia , `` resting on the ground '' ) is the superfamily of moths that contains the case - bearers , twirler moths , and relatives , also simply called curved - horn moths or gelechioid moths .
Anserimimus ( /ˌænsərᵻˈmaɪməs/ AN - sər - i - MY - məs ; `` goose mimic '' ) is a genus of ornithomimid theropod dinosaur , from the Late Cretaceous Period of what is now Mongolia .
Aetheolirion is a genus of monocotyledonous flowering plants in the dayflower family , first described in 1962 .
Brickelliastrum is a North American genus of flowering plants in the tribe boneset tribe within the sunflower fammily .
†Partula imperforata was a species of air - breathing tropical land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Partulidae .
Dolichamphilius brieni is a species of loach catfish endemic to the Democratic Republic of the Congo where it is found in Pool Malebo .
Sanzinia madagascariensis ( also known as the Malagasy tree boa , or Madagascar tree boa ) is a non - venomous boa species endemic to the island of Madagascar .
Congochromis is a genus of small cichlids native to river basins in Middle Africa .
Scaptotrigona mexicana is a species of stingless bee that lives throughout Mexico and is part of the Meliponini tribe .
Sargocentron tiere or the blue - lined squirrelfish is one species of Squirrelfish from the Indo - Pacific .
Paracanthocobitis mackenziei also known as the Robust zipper loach is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Paracanthocobitis .
Olybria aliculella is a species of snout moth , and the type species in the genus Olybria .
Hapalopilus croceus is a species of polypore fungus .
Cleistocactus hyalacanthus is a species of columnar cactus in the genus Cleistocactus .
Aphthona is a genus of beetle , in the leaf beetle family Chrysomelidae , native to Europe and Asia .
Iguanodontidae is a family of iguanodontians belonging to Styracosterna , a derived clade of the iguanodont group Ankylopollexia .
Archidistoma is a genus of tunicates .
Denticetopsis epa is a species of whale catfish endemic to Brazil where it is known from several localities in the lower portions of the Tocantins River basin .
Rhizospalax is a genus of extinct rodent from Europe thought to be distantly related to modern beavers .
Cyrtodactylus rubidus , or the red bow - fingered gecko , is a species of gecko found in the Andaman Islands ( India ) and the Coco Islands ( Myanmar ) .
Potamocorbula amurensis is a species of small saltwater clam , a marine bivalve mollusc in the order Myoida .
Haliotis australis , common name the `` queen paua '' or austral abalone , is a species of edible sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Haliotidae , the abalones .
Platyhypnidium riparioides , the long - beaked water feathermoss , is a species of aquatic moss commonly found in many regions .
Stenocorus meridianus is a species of longhorn beetle in the Lepturinae subfamily that can be found anywhere in Europe ( except for Faroe Islands , Iceland and Ireland , Malta , and parts of Italy such as San Marino , Sardinia , Sicily , and Vatican city ) , Caucasus , and Kazakhstan .
Caldesia is a genus of aquatic plants .
Dioryctria auranticella , the ponderosa pineconeworm moth , is a species of moth of the family Pyralidae .
Puccinia psidii can have very serious consequences to various species of plants in the Myrtaceae .
Estiella is a monotypic South African genus of potter wasps .
Lithoxus boujardi is a species of armored catfish endemic to French Guiana where it occurs in the Approuague and Oyapock River basins .
Astragalus asymmetricus is a species of milkvetch known by the common name San Joaquin milkvetch .
The Astrocoeniidae are a small family of stony corals .
Pinus durangensis , the Durango pine , is a pine tree species endemic to the Sierra Madre Occidental mountain range of Northwestern Mexico .
Tasmanophlebi lacuscoerulei is a species of mayfly in family Siphlonuridae .
The family is monogeneric , containing the single genus Gyroporus , which , according to a 2008 estimate , contains ten widely distributed species .
Bacteroides ureolyticus is a species in the bacterial genus of Gram - negative , obligately anaerobic bacteria .
Emarginula fissura , the common slit limpet , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Fissurellidae , the keyhole limpets .
Crossodactylodes ( common name : bromeliad frogs ) is a genus of leptodactylid frogs from the Atlantic Forest of eastern Brazil .
Mastixia arborea is a species of plant in the Cornaceae family .
Baru is an extinct genus of Australian mekosuchine crocodilian .
Chaerilus celebensis also known as the Asian bush scorpion or speckled bush scorpion is a species of scorpion from the family Chaerilidae .
Asarta alpicolella is a species of snout moth in the genus Asarta .
Thelephon is an extinct genus of procolophonine procolophonid parareptile from middle Triassic ( early Anisian stage ) deposits of Free State Province , South Africa .
Juncus regelii is a species of rush known by the common name Regel 's rush .
Micropterix trifasciella is a species of moth belonging to the family Micropterigidae that was described by Heath in 1965 , It is known from the French and Italian Alps , and is known to inhabit herbacious plants at an elevation range of 1,400 - -1,900 metres ( 4,600 - -6,200 ft ) .
Atheloca subrufella is a species of snout moth , a member of the genus Atheloca .
Graptemys is a genus of aquatic , freshwater turtles known commonly as map turtles or sometimes sawback turtles , endemic to North America .
Festuca brevipila , the hard fescue , is a species of grass which can be found everywhere in Canada and in both Eastern and Central United States ( except for Arkansas , Kansas , Nebraska , Oklahoma , and South Dakota ) .
Gentiana scabra ( or Japanese gentian ) is a species of flowering plant in the Gentian family ( Gentianaceae ) , found in much of the United States and Japan .
The Gulf Coast horned lizard ( Phrynosoma wigginsi ) is a horned lizard species native to Baja California , Mexico .
Acleisanthes nevadensis ( syn . Selinocarpus nevadensis ) is a species of flowering plant in the four o'clock family known by the common names desert moonpod and desert wing - fruit .
The Iberian wolf ( Canis lupus signatus ) is a subspecies of grey wolf that inhabits the forest and plains of northern Portugal and northwestern Spain .
Kukufeldia is a genus of iguanodont dinosaur that existed in what is now England during the Early Cretaceous period .
Nymphargus ruizi ( common name : Ruiz 's Cochran frog ) is a species of frog in the Centrolenidae family , formerly placed in Cochranella .
Lethrinus atkinsoni is a species of emperor fish described by Alvin Seale in 1910 .
Solanum tepuiense is a plant species native to Venezuela .
Agabus bipustulatus is a species of beetle native to the Palearctic ( including Europe ) , the Afro - tropical region , the Near East and North Africa .
Trypauchen is a genus of burrowing gobies native to the Indo - Pacific region .
Sulcavis is a genus of enantiornithine bird .
Callionymus sereti is a species of dragonet endemic to the Pacific Ocean around Futuna Island where it occurs at depths of from 245 to 400 metres ( 804 to 1,312 ft ) .
Erethistes pusillus is a species of South Asian river catfish native to India , Bangladesh and Myanmar where it is mostly found in hill streams .
Pseudoscopelus is a genus of snaketooth fishes .
Lockhartia micrantha is a species of orchid native to Nicaragua , Costa Rica , Panama and Colombia .
Montia is a genus of plants in the purslane family , Montiaceae .
Heterocapsa circularisquama is a species of Dinoflagellate notable for the production of a biotoxin affecting marine fauna .
Rubus cockburnianus ( white - stemmed bramble ) is a species of flowering plant in the family Rosaceae .
Locastra crassipennis is a species of snout moth in the genus Locastra .
Leptotyphlops sundewalli , or Sundevall 's worm snake , is a species of snake in the Leptotyphlopidae family .
Trichocoma is a genus of fungi in the family Trichocomaceae .
Catoxantha opulenta is a species of jewel beetles belonging to the family Buprestidae , subfamily Chrysochroinae .
Diplurus is a genus of prehistoric coelacanth fish which lived during the Triassic period .
Chrysomya rufifacies is a species belonging to the blow fly family , Calliphoridae , and is most significant in the field of forensic entomology due to its use in establishing or altering post mortem intervals .
